title: bess truman's ozark pudding
directions: Blend beaten egg and sugar together.
Add dry ingredients, then stir in nutmeats and apple.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly mix pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk and evaporated milk.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine and blend well, cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add all other ingredients except nuts.
Mix well and chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Cheese ball may be stored in refrigerator or freezer.

title: black joe cake
directions: Sift in bowl first 6 dry ingredients.
Blend in the eggs, oil, coffee and milk until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake, 2 (9-inch) rounds or 3 (8-inch) rounds.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Put first six ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan in order given. Pour condensed milk over top.
Bake in 325° oven for about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: beef jerky
directions: Slice brisket 1/4-inch thick and cut in 1 1/2-inch wide and 3-inch long strips.
Soak in mixture 15 hours.
Place oven on warm or lowest setting.
Put toothpick through one end of each piece and hang on oven rack.
Let dry for about 8 hours or until all moisture is gone.
For best results, leave oven door open about 1 1/2 inches while drying.

title: turkey fingers
directions: Combine eggs and pepper sauce.
Dip turkey into eggs, then bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Place between 2 sheets of wax paper and chill.
Fry for one minute until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Dip in Bleu cheese dressing or your choice of dressing.

title: shannon's no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper and let stand.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Drain and serve with chips.

title: party pizza
directions: Fry meat until crumbly; drain well.
Add ketchup and melted cheese.
Spread on bread.
Add pizza sauce, A.1.
sauce, oregano and garlic salt.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Freeze on cookie sheet and then store in plastic bags or cans.
When ready to use, bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sardi's rice pudding
directions: Bring rice and milk to a boil.
Simmer 50 minutes stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Beat together egg, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add hot milk and rice to egg mixture.
Stir well. Add cream.
Place raisins in bottom of baking dish; pour in rice mixture, stirring to distribute rice evenly.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in 350° oven in pan of water for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool, then chill.
(I find both cooking times need to be increased slightly.)

title: chicken and rice
directions: Wash rice.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt. Add milk and lay chicken on rice, skin side up, in single layer. In saucepan, mix soups and butter.
Heat until blended and butter melts.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and cook in oven for 2 hours at 275°.

title: chicken or turkey lattice pie
directions: In a saucepan, bring water, vegetable and bouillon to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 3 -5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and milk until smooth; add to the vegetable mixture.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 - 2 minutes or until thickened.
Add the turkey, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased 8 inch square baking dish.

title: hot beef dish
directions: Brown meat and onion in a frying pan.
Add other ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with crushed taco or Fritos chips.
Top with shredded cheese.
Heat in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: marinated fresh rattlesnake
directions: Skin the snake.
Fillet like a fish, slicing strips from the ribs.
Cut meat into 2-inch pieces and marinate for 3 hours in juice of oranges.
Add some lemon juice, peppercorns and dash of nutmeg.
Drain and wipe meat dry.
Sprinkle with salt.
Dip in beaten eggs and roll in fine bread crumbs.
Saute meat in hot butter until golden brown.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavorings.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add half at a time with milk.
Mix well.
Light oven, when you put in cake, at 350°.
Bake in stem pan, greased and floured.

title: 60 minute whole wheat rolls
directions: Mix water, honey, oil and yeast; let set for 10 minutes.
Add salt, eggs and flour; knead well.
Shape into rolls; let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon dump cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Dump into a greased Bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green onion dip(makes 2 cups)
directions: Blend in food processor until smooth.
Cover; chill.
Garnish with chopped green onions and serve on crackers.

title: chili rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Layer cheese between and on top.
Cover with foil and bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix syrup and bourbon until smooth.
Add dry ingredients. Roll into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and refrigerate.

title: butterscotch heavenly delight
directions: Even the most strong-willed dieter can't refuse a slice!

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a greased 3-quart baking dish, layer the sausage, onions, mushrooms, tomatoes and cheese.
In a large bowl, whisk the pancake mix, eggs, milk, oregano, salt and pepper; pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes or until top is set and lightly browned.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Yield; 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: *Can use crushed crackers, oatmeal (regular or quick), or bread crumbs (enough to firm up mixture so that it holds shape well).

title: lydia's turkey stroganoff
directions: In a bowl combine ground turkey, chili sauce, bread crumbs and garlic.
Form meat mixture into small balls.
In skillet heat 2 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Add meatballs and brown slowly.
After meatballs are brown, lower heat and cover for 15 minutes or until meatballs are firm when pressed with a fork.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender.
Add sour cream and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil brown sugar, Karo syrup, margarine, soda, vanilla and salt for 5 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour over popped corn (slowly) in a deep roasting pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight containers.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.

title: our favorite sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 25 minutes. Chop into small pieces. Mix chicken with cream of chicken soup, 1 1/2 pints of sour cream and green chilies. With an oil sprayer, spray a frying pan with a little oil and heat each tortilla until softened. Spread some creamed mixture down the middle of each tortilla (reserving some creamed mixture for topping).
Sprinkle some chopped onion and cheese on the filling of each tortilla (reserving some cheese for topping).

Roll up each tortilla and place seam side down in a greased pan. Pour remaining cream mixture over tortillas and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish with sliced olives, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain the broccoli as much as possible after cooking. Put broccoli in casserole dish; place the Cheez Whiz on top of broccoli. Crumble Ritz crackers on top of broccoli and cheese. Pour melted butter over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Serve with chips or vegetable sticks.

title: white chocolate lace basket
directions: Press a piece of foil firmly over outside of heart-shaped 8-inch cake pan.
Place pan in freezer.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt candy coating, stirring constantly until smooth. Cool slightly.
Pour melted coating into small squeeze bottle or pastry bag fitted with small writing tip.
Drizzle coating randomly over bottom and sides of foil pan; apply heavy coating around edges and corners.
Freeze for 30 minutes.
Unmold by carefully lifting foil from pan.
Carefully peel away from chocolate.
Place on tray.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Fill with candy or cookies.
Yields 1 basket.

title: rich rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water; stir and combine with cooled milk mixture.
Add about half the flour and beaten eggs and beat well.
Add enough of remaining flour to make a soft dough and mix thoroughly.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead about 10 minutes or until smooth and satiny.
Place dough in warm greased bowl; brush surface lightly with melted shortening or butter.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, 80° to 85°, about 2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Turn out on board and shape into rolls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise 1/2 to 3/4 hour or until doubled in size.
Brush with melted butter. Bake in moderate oven, 375°, for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramel zucchini bars
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Cream together the next 5 ingredients.
Add last 3 ingredients to dry ingredients. Mix together all ingredients.
Pour in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: gluten burger
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix together wet ingredients and add to wet.
Spray coffee can or equivalent canister with Pam. Place gluten in container and cover with wax paper. Pour one
inch of
water
in
crock-pot.
Place
canister
in crock-pot.
Cover and steam 4 hours on high.
Remove and cool. Slice or use in burger recipe.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix biscuit mix and milk together.
Fold and pat on floured board.
Rol into long roll.
Sprinkle 1 pound uncooked sausage onto dough.
Shape into a roll.
Cut into 1/2 inch pieces.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cottage cheese filling for kolaches
directions: Combine
ingredients and mix well.
When making cottage cheese kolaches, instead of making balls, spread the golf ball size dough
out
flat
to
about 1/4 inch thickness and place about
1 heaping teaspoonful of filling in center.
Then bring the
dough up to enclose the filling and pinch dough together to form
a ball.
Put pinched side of kolache on greased pan. Brush lightly with melted margarine.
Let rise in a warm place until
light, about
or 20 minutes.
Make a depression in center
of
each kolache
and
fill
with about 1 teaspoon of topping
(Posipka). Let rise again.
Bake at 350° about 15 or 20
minutes
or
until slightly
browned.
While
warm, brush lightly with melted margarine.

title: punch
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with dry mustard and sage.
Add water with bouillon cubes.
Bake at 300° for approximately 2 hours.

title: aunt nettie's blueberry cheesecake
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers, nuts and butter in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Pack into pan. In a bowl, beat eggs. Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and beat until smooth. Pour over crust. Bake at 325° for 15-20 minutes. Let cool. Spread 1 can blueberry pie filling over. Whip cream with sugar and vanilla. Top over cheesecake. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Melt yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add flour and stir into soft dough.
Keep in refrigerator with damp cloth over it.
Keeps up to 1 week.
When ready to cook, roll into ball.
Place in greased pan and let rise double.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snicker doodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together, add eggs and beat well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 8 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in a medium saucepan until tender.
Add zucchini and peppers; cook for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Discard bay leaf.
Store relish in airtight containers in refrigerator up to 5 days.
Yields 3 cups.

title: mother's day kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and salt.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Sprinkle sugar in gradually, a spoonful at a time.
Continue beating until the whites are very stiff.
Beat in vanilla.
Drop heaping spoons on baking sheets.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Makes about 30.

title: chicken divan
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add chicken.
Brown on both sides.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour and salt.
Make a smooth paste. Slowly add chicken broth, stirring until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in cream.
Put broccoli and chicken in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over it.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: lemon coconut surprise
directions: Drain
pineapple well.	Combine sour cream and pudding. Add coconut and pineapple; mix well.
Chill.
Garnish top with coconut and lemon slices before serving.

title: mandarin orange sweet potato salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil potatoes in jackets and set aside. Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon in a saucepan.
Add apricot nectar and orange rind.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Butter Buds.
Pour over sliced, peeled sweet potatoes and Mandarin oranges that have been placed in a casserole dish sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray. Sprinkle Grape-Nuts cereal on top.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: chicken licken good pork chops
directions: Combine flour, salt, dry mustard, garlic powder and place in Ziploc bag.
Coat pork chops and brown in skillet.
Place in crock-pot and add soups.
Heat for 8 hours on low or 6 hours on high.

title: meat gravy
directions: Chunk roast into 1-inch squares.
Put chunks into good sized pot.
Fill with water.
Boil beef 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until beef is real tender.
Prepare thickening in saucepan (flour, salt, pepper and enough warm water until thickened to medium consistency).
Add to beef soup to make gravy.

title: pistachio pudding jello
directions: Mix drained pineapple with dry pudding.
Stir in Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts and blend.
Put in pan and freeze in freezer.
Let set a few minutes before serving.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Sift salt, flour and baking powder together. Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Add vanilla, milk and dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Place dough on lightly floured board. Sprinkle a little flour over the dough and roll to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in a moderate 350° to 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oil. Add meat.
Cook. Stir in tomato sauce, crushed tomatoes, spaghetti mix and V-8 juice. Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Mix vegetables, onion and mayonnaise.
Layer the mixture and cheese in dish; top with crackers.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: english pea creole casserole
directions: Cook
celery,
onion
and
green pepper in butter until tender,
but not brown.
Add 1 can tomato soup.
Place remaining ingredients in layers in casserole and pour tomato mixture over all.
Cover top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or longer.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix the cookie mix as directed on package.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar; spread on cookie mix.
Arrange fruit in rows starting at center with kiwi.
Then go around with strawberries, then around with blueberries, etc.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: If using raw meat, preboil and rinse clean.
Pour kraut with juice into pot and cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Drain.
Put kraut in soup pot with 5 to 6 cups water, bay leaf, caraway seed and ham bone or ribs.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.

title: chuck's pork tenderloin
directions: Mix jelly, chili powder and catsup well.
Bake pork at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Baste with mixture several times while baking.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Put in soup and add milk.
Add grated cheese and put in.
Add already cooked macaroni, tuna and pimento.
Do this in skillet.
Transfer to casserole and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: skillet corn and chicken
directions: In skillet in hot margarine, brown chicken.
Remove.
Set aside and spoon off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients in skillet and heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and broccoli is tender-crisp, stirring often.
Garnish with tomato wedges and fresh thyme, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: frosting for german chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and boil until thick over medium heat.
Add chopped nuts and coconut.
You can add more coconut if not thick enough.
Good on any chocolate cake.

title: cottage cheese pancakes(makes approximately 16 pancakes)
directions: In a medium-sized bowl, combine beaten eggs (or substitute), cottage cheese, melted butter (or olive oil) and salt.
Sift together the flour; add to the other ingredients and mix.
Brown on a hot griddle in a mixture of melted butter and light olive oil.
Serve with fresh fruit, applesauce, jam, molasses or maple syrup.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Fold in half of the tub of whipped topping.
If desired, mix in a few mini chocolate chips.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Sprinkle with chips, confetti or colorful candies.

title: dream cake
directions: Mix together the diced apples and sugar and set aside for at least 10 minutes.
Beat eggs lightly and stir into the apple sugar mixture.
Then add dry ingredients; stir until thoroughly mixed, but be careful to not overmix.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake in a preheated oven for approximately 1 hour.
Shortly after removing cake from oven, prepare the following topping:

title: all american meat loaf
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; shape into 2 (7 1/2 x 4-inch) loaves.
Place on a lightly greased rack of a broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apricot whip
directions: Make Jell-O; chill until firm.
Whip drained apricots until puree form.
Mix with Jell-O; chill until ready to serve.
Serve in glass dishes.
Wine or parfait glasses look great.
Very good.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Bring first three ingredients to boil over medium heat until soft ball stage.
Pour over Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until forms small peaks.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: apricot coconut balls
directions: Put apricots and coconut in chopper (cut fine).
Mix in powdered sugar and roll in granulated sugar.
Let "ripen" in refrigerator at least a week.

title: macaroni-n-pea salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain and cool under cold water. Drain off all water, then add peas, 1/2 onion (chopped small), 1/2 jar (small) Miracle Whip and top with eggs, chopped or sliced.

title: apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla together until fluffy. Blend in remaining ingredients, except cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and onion in large bowl.
Add egg and milk stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Let batter stand 5 minutes.

title: custard
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; add scalded milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Set casserole in pan of water (about 1-inch deep).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until silver knife inserted comes out clean.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine, cover and chill for minimum of 3 hours.
Salad is better if chilled overnight.
Low-fat mayonnaise may be used.

title: 1-2-3-4 casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Place in bottom of 3-quart casserole dish.
Then add layer of onions (sliced thin).
Spread one can of soup over onions.
Next, layer carrots (sliced very thin) and finish up with potatoes (also sliced very thin).
Spread second can of soup on top of potatoes.
Cover dish and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: b & b salad
directions: Cut up the broccoli and cauliflower; place in a large bowl. Fry the bacon and drain.
Fry the onion and drain.
Place in bowl with other ingredients.
Chop the cheese and green or red pepper.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and butter until golden shade.
Pour syrup over popcorn.
Mix together.
Pour mix onto cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break up.

title: drop in salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine the first four ingredients. Combine vinaigrette and lemon juice; drizzle over salad. Toss to coat. Serve immediately. Yield 8-10 servings.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in cocoa, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased pan. Refrigerate until cold, then cut in squares.

title: company mashed potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes.
Beat until smooth.
Add salt and pepper, then cream cheese and beat again.
Blend in onion, eggs, flour and parsley and beat again.
Turn into buttered casserole dish. Spread crushed onion over top and bake at 325°
for 30 minutes.

title: new sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together well the cream cheese and beaten eggs.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Spread mixture into crusts and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Meanwhile, mix pudding with the milk. Fold in potatoes, cinnamon and Cool Whip.
Blend well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla together.
Add flour, oats and soda.
Blend well.
Pinch off into small balls and flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk and cool to lukewarm.
Combine yeast, milk and one teaspoon of sugar in a large bowl.
Sift in 1/2 cup of flour.
Stir until flour is dampened.
Cover bowl with a clean cloth and set in a warm place for about one hour.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill 2 hours and serve.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add beaten egg. Add lukewarm water and mix well with wooden spoon.
Add bread.
Mix well and roll into oblong dumplings or in 2 pieces if desired. Place in boiling water. Cover and cook about 10 minutes on one side.
Turn over and cook on the other side.
Cut with string.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Sift-measure flour.
Sift again with the other dry ingredients. Combine milk, slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, beating until smooth.
Cover dough tightly and chill overnight or until cold.
Turn dough onto floured surface and roll out to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out with round cookie cutter or into squares with a knife.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in hot oven at 425°.
Cool.
They will be crisp when cool.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Stir in milk and juice.
Beat one egg white until stiff and fold into the filling.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Beat remaining 3 egg whites, adding sugar 1 tablespoon at a time, until thick and glossy.
Spread meringue over filling, making sure it touches the edges of crust.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, 24 marshmallows and 1 cup milk.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add coconut.
Place on cake as soon as out of oven.
Let cool.
Place 1/4 cup margarine, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup milk in pan.
Bring to boil.
Stir in chocolate chips. Top cake with chip mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly, then roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: chocolate fondue supreme
directions: Combine cocoa, cornstarch and salt and blend with butter until smooth.
Add milk and sugar substitute and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Put pan in cool ice water and stir until cool. Yield:
16 tablespoons.
Carbohydrate 2 g, protein .7 g, fat 1 g, calories 17.
Free food exchange.

title: mexican cottage cheese sauce(use as a dressing on lettuce wedge or as a dip)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: meat loaf #1
directions: Mix all together good and shape.
Put into pan.
Cook in a preheated 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Will be brown.
Drain and cool before slicing.

title: chinese dish
directions: Brown and
cook meat in shortening; add celery, onions, water and mushrooms with liquid.
Mix soy sauce and cornstarch together, then gradually pour in cooked ingredients to thicken.
Add drained bean sprouts.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients in ungreased pan.
Make a well and put in the vinegar, vanilla, oil and water.
Mix well.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips, walnuts and sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: karo buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter; add Karo syrup, salt and sugar alternately, beating until smooth.
Add enough milk to make frosting of spreading consistency.

title: lemon poke cake
directions: Bake cake in a large dish according to directions on box of cake mix.
Cool thoroughly.
Pierce cake with fork at 1/2 inch intervals.
Stir 4 cups of boiling water into the lemon Jell-O and stir for 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Carefully pour hot mixture over cake.
Cool in the refrigerator.
Then pour 1 cup cold milk into bowl; add 1 package (4 serving size) lemon flavor instant pudding and powdered sugar.
Beat with a wire whisk 2 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and spread on cake.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Ice when cool.
For best results, refrigerate mix overnight and bake the next day.

title: basic pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients then add eggs and milk.
gradually add the oil.
You can add blueberries, or cooked rice or tsp. of cinnamon and 2 Tbsp. sugar.
Pour onto griddle heated with a small amount of heat.
When cooked on edges, turn, cook for about 1 minute more.
Remove and serve immediately.

title: gregary's chocolate mousse
directions: Whip the cream and chocolate syrup until stiff.
Fold in sugar and brandy.
Chill in champagne glasses.

title: tiny's pie crustdallas, texas
directions: Blend the flour and Crisco and salt.
Add egg, vinegar and enough water to make a dough.
Roll out on a floured wax paper. Bake at 350° until brown or fill and bake.
This recipe makes 4 single crusts.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix all together (adding nuts and chips last).
Batter will be very stiff.
Spread in an 11 x 17-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: quick veggie casserole
directions: Heat the cheese, soup, milk and butter.
Pour over veggies and rice.
Bake in buttered casserole for 1 hour.

title: easy cocoa pudding
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Mix until smooth with 1 cup milk. In a large iron skillet, scald the rest of the milk.
Add the cornstarch mixture.
Stir constantly until it boils and thickens. Stir in margarine.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion until meat is slightly browned.
Drain. Add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Turn into pan.
Cut cheese into 3-inch strips; place over meat.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lentil-ham soup
directions: Rinse lentils.
Combine lentils and water in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Stir cubed ham, carrots, onion, bay leaf, pepper, marjoram and garlic powder into lentils in the Dutch oven.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, about 30 minutes or until lentils are tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes and parsley.
Heat through.
Discard bay leaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine lime Jell-O, pineapple and sugar. Boil for 3 minutes. Let cool. Whip Dream Whip. Add cottage cheese. Whip well. Add the Jell-O mixture. Fold in pecans. Put in serving dish. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.

title: confetti meat loaf
directions: In a medium bowl combine first 5 ingredients.
In a foil-lined baking pan, shape beef mixture into an 8 x 5-inch loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
If desired, serve with tomato sauce.

title: salsa
directions: Mix with pastry blender everytime you add something else. Start with drained tomatoes, then the chopped onions, green chilies, jalapenos, Crisco, olive oil and salt.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and crabmeat.
Spread in dish, then top this with cocktail sauce.
Eat with crackers.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well; add the remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: reese's twinkles
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate bar and 1/2 cup peanut butter and set aside.
Melt remaining 1 cup peanut butter in microwave only until soft.
Place 1 package bake cups in muffin pans and fill 1/4 with chocolate mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm.
Repeat with peanut butter and remaining chocolate (close enough to fool the experts).
Makes about one dozen.

title: pickled carrots and zucchini
directions: In saucepan mix sugar, vinegar, water, mustard seed, cinnamon and cloves.
Add carrots, cover and simmer until carrots are crisp-tender.
Add zucchini strips, return to boiling.
Transfer mixture to bowl.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In large bowl combine 2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, shortening and salt until warm.
Add eggs.
Beat at low speed with mixer about 1/2 minute, then continue beating at high speed for 3 minutes.
By hand, stir in 1 1/2 to 2 cups flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface for 8 to 10 minutes.
Shape into ball.
Cover.
Let raise until double.
Punch down and divide in half.
Cover and let raise about 10 minutes. Roll out and spread with preferred filling.
Place into prepared pans and let raise until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
24 rolls.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter over low heat and add flour gradually.
Stir until no longer lumpy.
Add next 6 ingredients gradually, stirring. Stir until no lumps are left; salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until it comes to a boil, then lower heat.
Cover and let it simmer until the potatoes are done.
Makes 12 servings; 190 calories and 2 grams fat.

title: chili cornbread casserole
directions: Cover 8-inch square baking dish with 1-inch of your favorite chili.
Top with cheese.
Mix cornbread mix with evaporated milk. Pour on top of chili and cheese.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Take the chicken meat off bone and put broth in refrigerator to let fat separate.
When ready to make soup, skim fat from broth and put in kettle.
Heat to boiling and add the onion, celery and okra.
Cook until barely tender.
Add tomatoes and chicken, cut up.
Season with chicken bouillon, salt and pepper.
Add rice. This will make enough for 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover bottom

of large baking dish with chicken pieces. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Crumble crackers over mixture. Drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and tender.

title: hot pork chops
directions: Dip tomatoes and peppers into a pan of very hot grease until the skins burn loose; then remove peels and mash tomatoes and peppers.
Brown the pork chops in about 2 tablespoons grease.
Add tomatoes and mix when pork chops are thoroughly browned.
Let simmer about 30 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste (salt, pepper, garlic, paprika and chili powder).

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine eggs and liquids in a bowl. Beat into dry ingredients.
Cook on hot griddle using 2 tablespoons of batter for each pancake.

title: pork chops in sauce
directions: In skillet brown chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top chops with onions.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over chops.
Simmer 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Peel, cut and cube the eggplant; leave soaking in water with salt for 15 minutes.
Saute in pan 1/2 of the garlic in olive oil. Drain eggplant well and add to garlic.
Cook until eggplant is soft.
Dissolve the flour in 1/2 cup water, then add to eggplant. Stir until thickens.
Mash with fork.
Add the other 1/2 of garlic, salt and mayonnaise.
Serve with onion pita bread.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix together; place in casserole and cover with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° or until crumbs are brown.

title: triple chocolate brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle remaining chips on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: punch for at least 100
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; heat and stir until combined and sugar melts.
Freeze in shallow pans (such as jelly roll pans). May be made days in advance.
When ready to serve, spoon out individual portions in large punch bowl.
Pour 7-Up or ginger ale over the frozen portions.
Keeps well in freezer for days or as long as it lasts.

title: pink shrimp dip
directions: Mix together all the ingredients; let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour and serve with crackers.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press on bottom and 1/4-inch up sides of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Pour over shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix the last 3 ingredients well.
Pour over cake. Refrigerate when cool.

title: norwegian meat balls and noodles
directions: Cut onion in small pieces and saute in 2 tablespoons of oil or butter for a few minutes.
Then add the remaining ingredients. Form into meatballs and brown in oil or butter until done.
Add meatballs to a can of golden mushroom soup and simmer a few minutes.
Serve over your favorite noodles.

title: venison stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Brown meat; add onions, garlic, Worcestershire, bay leaf, oregano, salt, pepper and 3 cups water. Simmer, covered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add potatoes and carrots and continue cooking about 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Mix flour and cold water; stir into stew until thickened.
Heat until bubbly hot.
Add browning sauce if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well:
Cream cheese, milk, peanut butter and sugar. Blend in Cool Whip.
Fold into pie shell.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: meatball cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs to creamed margarine and sugar.
Add all dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls about 1-inch in diameter. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Roll twice in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: new orleans red beans and rice
directions: Cook together.
Before serving, add 3 cups of cooked rice.

title: apple pecan coffee cake
directions: In large bowl, cream together shortening, sugar and eggs with an electric mixer.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, 1/4 teaspoon salt and cinnamon.
Add to the cream mixture.
Stir in apples and pecans (batter will be thick).
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until firm in the middle.

title: papa's country chicken soup
directions: Quarter and boil chicken with salt, pepper and onion and garlic powders until done.
Remove chicken.
Let cool; strain broth.
Add vegetables (celery, carrots and onion).
Let cook until real tender.
Debone chicken, cut into bite-size pieces. Add cream of chicken soup to vegetables and let dissolve.
Add chicken and cooked noodles.
Let simmer for 10 minutes, then serve.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, olives, chilies and 1 teaspoon picante sauce.
Spread on flour tortillas and roll up.
Refrigerate at least one hour.
Slice into 3/4-inch slices.
Insert toothpicks and dip into picante sauce for serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together, except barbecue sauce.
Shape into medium size balls.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over each ball.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream of squash soup
directions: Combine butter and oil in a large Dutch oven.
Add onion and garlic; saute until tender.
Stir in squash and chicken broth; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon a third of squash mixture into container of electric blender and process until smooth. Repeat with remaining squash mixture.

title: aunt dene's chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones and skin.
Place chicken in casserole.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Mix flour and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix the soup and broth together. Pour over the other mixture.
Cook in 350° oven until thickened.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Mix together.
This makes enough filling for one sandwich loaf of bread.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into 1 large ball or 2 smaller balls.
Roll cheese ball in chopped nuts.

title: butterscotch yams
directions: Arrange yams in single layer in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. In a saucepan, stir together brown sugar, corn syrup, cream, margarine, salt and cinnamon.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over yams.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 minutes, basting once.

title: homemade wine
directions: Soak sugar and yeast in warm water until yeast dissolves.
Add frozen grape juice.
Mix together and pour in gallon jug.
Fill up to neck with water.
Place a wide neck balloon on neck of jug. When balloon goes down the wine is ready (about 30 days).
Keep jug in a cool place.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and
catsup to a slow boil, mixing well. Mix a little
cornstarch
and water together and add to sauce. Use small
amounts and repeat until desired thickness. This is excellent on anything you can put it on.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Grate cheese, chop onion and pepper. Add all ingredients to potatoes, except corn flake crumbs and butter.
Mix and pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: cereal bars
directions: Mix syrup, cream and sugar in a pan and cook to firm ball stage.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Makes a large pan of bars.

title: esther's favorite christmas fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine and mix all the dry ingredients in a heavy 4-quart saucepan; stir in milk.
Bring to a bubbly boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring to 234° (to a soft ball stage).
Remove from heat and add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110°. Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread on a lightly buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan, let cool and cut into squares.

title: zucchini casserole(serves 6)
directions: Combine zucchini and onion in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Cover.
Cook in countertop microwave oven, about 15 minutes or until zucchini is tender.
Stir every 3 minutes.
Drain.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel, slice and boil carrots until tender-crisp.
Drain well. Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well in fridge. Flavor gets better with age!

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add 10x sugar 1/2 cup at a time. Beat in vanilla and milk.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach leaves into medium pieces.
Add tomato wedges, sliced onion rings and eggs; toss.
Serve in salad bowls with poppy seed dressing.
(Recipe in cookbook.)

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in bowl.
Add eggs and buttermilk; stir until blended.
Stir in butter and vanilla and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: sandies
directions: Add vanilla to margarine, then confectioners sugar and cream until mixture is fluffy.
Add water to creamed mixture, then gradually add flour to mixture and last add your pecans.
Shape dough into small balls, about 1/2-inch thick.
Place rolls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Do not brown!
Take out and roll through some confectioners sugar as desired.

title: minted peas
directions: Shell peas and combine with onion, sugar, salt, mandarin peel and mint.
Add a small amount of water, cover and cook until barely tender.
Water should be evaporated when peas are done. Remove mint sprig, toss peas with butter, serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: chicken convention
directions: If not using croutons, trim, butter and cube slices of toast. Put half of bread cubes on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Saute green pepper, onion, celery and pimiento; mix with mayonnaise and cooked chicken.
Spread mixture over bread cubes; then cover with remaining cubes.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove; spread soup over casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven for 30 more minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serves about 8.

title: kodiak casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown ground beef with onions and garlic; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until hot and bubbly. Sprinkle with the cheese just before serving.
Yield:
16 to 20 servings.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Pour in milk; mix lightly with a fork.
Turn out on board and knead about 1 minute. Roll dough thin (about thickness of a cookie).
Spread with the sausage.
Roll up as a jelly roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill for several hours.
Remove wrap and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Yields approximately 40 pinwheels.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cut shrimp into very small pieces along with eggs.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: nanie and charlene's orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to creamy mixture.
Place flour in large bowl.
Add dates, orange candy and nuts.
Stir to coat.
Add flour and coconut to mixture.
This will make a stiff mixture and should be mixed by hand.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
After cake is done, mix Glaze.

title: meat loaf(he even asks for it!!)
directions: Mix all ingredients until mixture sticks to your hands.
Shape mixture into a rounded square and place on a baking pan sprayed with vegetable spray.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: ranger crispies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl, cream margarine, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until blended.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and vanilla to creamed mixture. Stir until well blended.
Stir in crisp rice cereal.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute before removing from pan.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream together for 3 minutes. Pour 1/2 mixture in greased 9 x 13 pan. Mix 1 c. brown sugar and cinnamon. Pour over first half. Pour rest of cake mixture over top. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes. Punch holes in cake while it is still hot. Mix powdered sugar, milk and vanilla. Pour over cake and enjoy!

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Lightly beat fruit cocktail juice with eggs.
Add oil and liquid to dry mixture and mix well. Fold in fruit cocktail.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
In a separate bowl, mix brown sugar and orange or lemon juice. Dribble over baked cake.
Top with pecans.
Bake another 10 minutes. Cake will be moist when done.

title: slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrot in bowl.
Dice tomatos in same bowl. Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt butter.
Add chocolate chips.
When melted, add peanut butter.
When all is smooth and creamy, pour over cereal.
Stir gently until all cereal is coated.
Shake with powdered sugar (grocery bag or large bowl) until completely covered.
Store, uncovered, until cool.

title: chicken with basil cream sauce
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cut each chicken breast in half.
Pour milk into pie plate.
Place bread crumbs on waxed paper.
Dip chicken breasts into milk, then into bread crumbs to coat.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In medium saucepan, mix gelatine and 2 tablespoons of the sugar.
Blend in egg yolks, beaten with lemon juice and water. Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Stir in corn syrup and lemon peel.
Pour into large bowl and chill.
Stir occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.

title: dried apple stack cake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease seven 9 inch round pans.
Cream shortening and sugar together; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir buttermilk, baking soda, baking powder together and mix into batter.
Blend in flour and salt; pour into cake pans.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Stack layers with hot apple filling between them.

title: guaranteed no-lump gravy
directions: Measure oil into skillet.
Measure sifted flour into small bowl.
Measure milk in large container to warm (works best if milk is not ice cold).
Heat oil to hot.
While stirring with slotted spoon, sprinkle flour into oil and continue stirring.
Cook until turns golden brown, lower heat.
While stirring, slowly pour in milk.
Continue stirring and heat until thick, will thicken some as it cools.
Trick is continuous stirring with slotted spoon.
Same trick will work with any gravy.

title: london broil marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then pierce your London Broil. Lay London Broil on mixture.
Turn every hour for 4 hours.
Then broil your London Broil to your preferred doneness.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender.
Add 6 cups water and noodles. Cook until noodles are tender.
Add broccoli and garlic powder. Add milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: potatoes and cheese
directions: Mix
everything
together,
except
milk, oleo and corn flakes.
Melt
oleo and add milk.
Put potato mixture in a 9 x 12-inch pan
and
pour the oleo and milk mixture over it.
Top with corn flakes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat; cover and braise until tender.
Put in large kettle with molasses and rinse jar with water for liquid.
Add chopped celery and onions.
Slowly cook, covered, for 1 hour. Season to taste, stirring often.
Add drained vegetables.
Fifteen minutes before serving, add cornstarch mixed with 1/2 cup water. Serve with rice and/or chow mein noodles.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Arrange tomato slices in a long baking dish.
In bowl, mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, oregano and green onions.
Spoon dressing over tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours.
Makes 10 servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water overnight or bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes; turn off heat, cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: tuna lunch
directions: Mix ingredients and serve over a bed of lettuce with saltine crackers.
Makes 2 servings.

title: orange-pineapple slush
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well to blend.
Pour mixture into a freezer tray or an 8-inch square baking pan and freeze until almost firm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream Crisco.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: MIx first 3 ingredients and let set overnight.
Next day add apples, grapes, walnuts and salt.
Fold cream or Cool Whip into mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cold gazpacho
directions: Skin tomatoes by plunging them into boiling water. Leave for 1 to 2 minutes.
Then plunge them into cold water and peel off skins.
Then place tomatoes in blender.
Remove seeds from pepper. Chop and add to tomatoes.
Peel and chop cucumber and onion.
Add with the garlic and egg to the ingredients in the blender. Measure remaining ingredients into blender.
Cover and liquidize thoroughly.
Add cold water to thin.
Pour soup into bowl.
Serve immediately.
Takes 20 minutes to make.
Good source of Vitamin A and C.

title: peanut butter nut cake(tube or sheet cake)
directions: Put raisins and soda in hot water to cover 1 inch over raisins.
Let stand until cool, about 2 hours.
Mix sugar, peanut butter and eggs. Mix well.
Add flour, allspice and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: 1800's spice cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until creamed; add eggs and milk.
Add flour until thick enough to roll into little balls.
Roll in sugar and place on cookie pan and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pasta and clams
directions: Simmer the olives, clam juice, chopped bacon, bacon grease and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add butter and simmer 15 minutes.
Add clams and simmer 5 minutes.
Toss mix over linguine.
Toss parsley or Parmesan cheese.

title: luby's shredded carrots
directions: *To plump raisins, soak in water and drain before using.

title: mackerel patties
directions: Drain juice from mackerel into a bowl.

Debone mackerel under slow running water and drain. Break up mackerel into bowl of juice, add the egg and crackers, mix well. Shape into eight patties. Cook in a well buttered skillet and top with a pat of butter on uncooked side. Brown on both sides.

title: peanut butter rite sandwich
directions: On one piece of bread, put the peanut butter.
Split the Ritz in half and spread on the bread.
Put it together and enjoy.

title: kathy's favorite pie crust recipe
directions: In a large bowl, cut shortening into flour using a knife or pastry cutter until coarse and crumbly.
Add beaten egg, ice water and vinegar.
Mix together and work into a dough.
Makes two 9-inch pie crusts.

title: creamy lime fruit and nut salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O in mixing bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly, then stir in milk. Cool until partially set, stirring frequently, while cooling to keep smooth. Fold in remaining ingredients. Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm (2 to 3 hours). Cut in squares and serve.

title: greek bread
directions: Melt butter and mix in other ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
Spread on bread and cook until melted.

title: gobbler snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread until well blended.
Place this mixture on rye slices.
Place on cookie sheet and broil a couple of minutes until bubbly.
Watch carefully.
Serve hot.

title: pork scallop
directions: Wash and pare potatoes.
Cut in thin slices.
Cook tomatoes, onions, sugar, salt, pepper and shortening for 10 minutes.
Put a layer of potatoes in a baking dish and cover with some of the tomato mixture.
Add another layer of potatoes and repeat until all ingredients are used.
Trim off excess fat on pork chops and lay on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling on bottom; spread evenly.
Put pineapple on top of cherry pie filling; spread evenly.
Put dry cake mix on top. Put 2 sticks of oleo on top and spread evenly (sliced or melted). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Put pecans or walnuts on top.
Add a dab of Cool Whip, ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 20.

title: crock pot turkey breast
directions: Place turkey breast down in crock pot.
Combine melted margarine or butter, lemon juice and Italian salad dressing and pour over turkey breast.
Cook all day on low.

title: one pan chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix, bake and serve all in same 8-inch square pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Put flour, granulated sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt into ungreased 8-inch square baking pan.
Stir with fork to mix well.
Add milk and oil; stir until well blended.
Sprinkle brown sugar, remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and the chocolate chips over the batter.
Mix vanilla with water; pour evenly over top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until surface looks dry and brownie like. Serve with a spoon warm or at room temperature.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and place in two-quart microwave casserole.
Set aside.
Place butter in four cup measure.
Microwave for one minute or until melted.
Stir in flour until blended.
Pour milk into two cup glass measure and cook in microwave for three minutes.
Stir in flour-butter mixture. Cook six to eight minutes or until thickened, stirring frequently. Add salt and onion.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Pour over macaroni.
Blend well.
Serve immediately.

title: polish mazurki
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend sugar, butter and flour.
Pat and press mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool. Spread baked layer with jam.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and spread over jam.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in saucepan until thick.
Pour into baked pie crusts. Cover filling with meringue. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: *turkish coffee(cafea turteasca)
directions: Place water in brass Turkish coffee maker or small saucepan. Add sugar and coffee. Stir vigorously.
Place over heat and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat until foam goes down, then replace over heat. Repeat twice. Skim 1 teaspoon of foam into each demitasse cup and pour remaining coffee into cups.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put nuts all around mound. Refrigerate for a few hours.
Use as spread with assorted crackers.

title: comfort eggnog
directions: Chill all liquids before mixing.
Separate eggs; beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar. Stir in all milk and Cool Whip.
Add whiskey.
Fold in egg whites. Chill.
Dust with nutmeg, if desired.
Serves 10.

title: deep dish fruit pie
directions: Pit, peel and slice fruit.
Mix together and place in deep 8-inch baking dish with the white sugar and lemon juice.
Bake at 375° until fruit is tender (about 45 minutes for apples).
With pastry blender, mix together flour, brown sugar, oil and cinnamon until it is crumbly.
Place atop cooked fruit and continue to bake until brown and bubbly.
Top each serving with ice milk or sherbet.
Yield:
6 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients, except nuts, in a large microwavable bowl.
Microwave at Medium (50%) until chocolate chips are melted, 3 to 5 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking time. Remove from microwave and stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased square dish, 8 x 8-inch.
Refrigerate until set.
Yields about 2 pounds.

title: broken glass dessert
directions: Dissolve each of the first three Jell-Os separately in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour in separate pans (9 x 9-inch or such).
Refrigerate until solid.

title: rapid raspberry torte
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream until soft peaks form. Add powdered sugar; beat until stiff peaks form. Place pudding in a different bowl, and then fold in whipping cream. Split cake in 3 horizontal layers. Spread half of jam over bottom layer; repeat layers. Top with third cake layer cut into slices. Top with pudding mixture. 7-10 serving.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix eggs and milk, then add onion, cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Add zucchini.
Fry in hot butter in skillet until brown on both sides.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in raisins.

title: ma's sop chocolate
directions: In medium saucepan, thoroughly mix sugar, cocoa and flour. Gradually add milk until mixture is well blended.
Add boiling water.
Cook on medium heat until mixture reaches desired thickness.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla flavoring, stirring until butter is melted.
Serve warm or cold and "sop" with biscuits, bread, rolls, etc. of your choice.
Yields enough for 5 or 6 people.

title: bacon and tomato canapes
directions: Hollow out tomatoes and drain upside down on paper towels overnight.
Fry bacon crisp.
DRAIN WELL.
Crumble, mix with other ingredients and fill tomato shells.

title: hot crab dip(serves 10)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise in a large bowl; stir in lemon juice, pepper sauce and scallions.
Fold in chopped crabmeat, salt and pepper.
Spread in baking dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly and top is golden. Serve hot or warm.

title: natalie's bake beans
directions: Brown onion and pepper in 1 tablespoon bacon grease until tender.
Cook all ingredients until thick.

title: brown sugar squash
directions: Clean squash and cut in half.
Clean out seeds with a spoon. Remove stem.
Fill a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with 1/4 cup water. Place squash upside-down in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. While squash is baking, melt butter in pan.
Stir in brown sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Leave mixture on low heat until 1/2 hour is up. Take out squash, turn them right side up and fill them with butter mixture.
Place squash back in oven for 1/2 hour.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix pimento, onion, cheese, pickles and eggs lightly.
Add peas and salt to taste.
Mix with enough salad dressing to hold all ingredients together.
Be careful not to mash peas when mixing.
Chill well.
Serve on lettuce leaves or alone as a vegetable.
Be sure to use LeSueur peas.
This is the secret to this recipe.

title: crackers
directions: Sift dry ingrediments...heat the milk 'n shortenin'...mix up the aig 'n the flour mixture 'n work on til well blended...now dump in melted shortenin' 'n milk...mix til hit makes a stiff dough...this you beats wid a rollin' pin til the dough pops when broken.
Now divide in bout 4 parts 'n roll each part az thin az papur...stick reel gud wid a fork 'n cut in strips 'n sections lak a sto' bought cracker.
Bake at 300° til a reel delikate brown color.
They's ready!

title: party potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil until tender and drain.	Beat softened cream cheese and sour cream at medium speed until well blended.
Add hot potatoes gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add chives and toss carefully.
Put in a 2 quart greased casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake
325° for 25 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes.
Combine meal, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dredge tomatoes in this and fry in skillet, with a 1/4-inch of oil, until brown, turning once.
Serves 6.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix oil, dressing mix and garlic powder and pour over oyster crackers.
Mix real good.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef
or
turkey.
Drain and mix with taco seasoning according
to
directions.
Tear
head of lettuce into bite-size pieces
and
put
in very large (7 quart) salad bowl or large
roasting
pan.
In another bowl mix the drained can of
kidney
beans,
salsa, tomatoes, avocados and olives. This mixture
can be made up to 6 hours in advance, if refrigerated. Crush
the
Doritos
in
the bag and combine the meat mixture, vegetable
mixture,
chips
and lettuce together and serve right away.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Cut off crusts from bread and cube bread.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cube cream cheese and spread over bread cubes. Beat eggs; beat in maple syrup and milk.
Pour over cubes in pan; cover with plastic wrap and store overnight in refrigerator.
When ready to use, bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together (do not use beater), then add apples and pecans and mix well.
Then add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Batter will be stiff.
Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spaghetti puttanesca
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic; stir.
Remove pan from heat and allow hot oil to turn garlic pale gold (5 to 10 minutes).
Stir in tomatoes, capers, olives, red pepper flakes, basil, oregano and black pepper.
Return to medium-low heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper, if needed.
Reduce heat to very low.

title: peanut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan.
Put the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Add the peanut butter, milk and egg.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon into the pan and bake for about 50 minutes.
Remove from the pan and cool on a rack.

title: betty's brown bread
directions: Mix 4 cups flour with dry ingredients.
Add raisins, mixing them with fingers to separate.
Add buttermilk and mix with fork until mixture forms a dough.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup flour on surface, turn out and knead dough about 5 minutes.
Form into smooth, round loaf.

title: grandma's cherry dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add melted butter or margarine.
Press half of the mix on bottom of pan.
Add cherry pie filling.
Put remaining crumbs on top of cherries.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: salad
directions: Chop all ingredients and toss, then pour on your favorite dressing.

title: walnut cake
directions: Beat the egg yolk until very light; add the sugar gradually and beat well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt; add the nuts and then combine with egg mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in the stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Bake in 2 layer cake tins in a moderate 350° oven from 30 to 40 minutes.

title: holden village eggs florentine
directions: Saute chopped onion.
Stir in spinach and season with garlic salt and pepper to taste. Spread mixture in pie pan.
Make 8 indentations for eggs.
Break raw eggs into indentations.
Cover with Mornay Sauce. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Beat eggs with water.
Add cake, pudding mixes and melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips. Bake for 50 minutes at 325° in buttered and floured pan.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box; drain and let cool.
Mix the cucumbers, tomatoes and onion with cooled spaghetti.
Pour dressing over all, toss and sprinkle with Salad Delight seasoning. Refrigerate and serve.

title: rich peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt peanut butter and margarine in bowl over hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cool cake completely.
In blender, mix vanilla pudding with 1 cup of milk.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold in pineapple and coconut.
Spread on cake and chill.

title: imperial pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add flour and blend.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan or two large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: In small bowl with fork, mash the Blue cheese.
Gradually work in the sour cream, buttermilk and vinegar.
Add salt and pepper. Add oil; beat hard, preferably with a wire whip, to make as smooth as possible.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Put in jar, cover tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix in bowl sugar, flour and eggs.
Add pineapple, coconut, walnuts and soda.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: grilled salmon with lime butter
directions: In glass or stainless steel bowl, combine lime juice and ginger root; add salmon and let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes, turning fillets over every 5 minutes.
In small bowl, combine butter and lime peel; set aside.
Spray grill or fish basket with nonstick cooking spray.
Grill salmon approximately 10 minutes per inch or until flaky.
Remove from grill.
Spread immediately with lime butter.

title: orange vanilla wafer balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Press into balls; let dry 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 40.
Especially nice when you need cookies, the weather is hot and you don't want to use the oven.

title: peanut butter rocky road dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Refrigerate candies to make cutting easier.
Mix butter and graham cracker crumbs well.
Press into bottom of a 9 inch square pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, in medium bowl, mix first 5 ingredients and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Shape beef mixture into 1-inch meatballs.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook meatballs until browned on all sides; removing meatballs to bowl as they brown.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons dripping from skillet.
Cut cream cheese into chunks.
To drippings, add cream cheese, remaining ingredients, and 1/8 teaspoon salt; cook over low heat, stirring with wire whisk or spoon until melted and smooth.
Return meatballs to skillet; heat, stirring occasionally. Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: quick and easy banana nutbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9
x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and blend.	Stir in bananas.
Mix flour, soda and salt and stir in.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: white taffy candy
directions: Cook all together, except vanilla, without stirring, until candy forms hard ball stage when tried in cold water, or reaches 250°.
Remove from heat.
Pour onto buttered platter.
When cool, pull until creamy white, working in the vanilla.
Stretch into long strips about the size of a finger.
Cut into 1-inch lengths. Wrap in waxed paper.

title: dry apples for art projects
directions: Slice apples into 1/4-inch circles.
Soak in lemon juice for at least 20 minutes.
Bake at 150° for 6 hours.
Bake on a wire screen or oven rack.
Do not place on a cookie sheet.
Turn off oven before apples turn brown.
Open oven door and allow apples to cool gradually.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes and 1/2 cup of butter with other ingredients; pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes and butter (use 1 1/2 cups of flakes and 1/4 cup butter).
Bake at 300° for 1 or 1 1/2 hours.

title: family favorite
directions: Prepare dinner as directed.
Brown meat, drain and add onions and green pepper; cook until tender.
Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: With electric beater, mix until very stiff the egg whites, sugar, vanilla, salt and cream of tartar.
Fold in the pecans. Grease a 9-inch pie pan. Turn mixture into pan, forming a nest on bottom and up on sides. Bake at 300° for 55 minutes. Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter to soften.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add syrup and salt; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Hand stir in peanuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: ribbon jello salad
directions: Bring milk to a boil and add sugar until dissolved.
Add Knox gelatine.
Also add sour cream and vanilla.
Mix with electric mixer.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam or oil pan.
Make Jell-O, one box at a time.
Each layer will need to set.
Add a milk layer between each jello layer.
Finish top with milk layer.

title: fruitcake squares
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle evenly with crumbs.
Sprinkle next four ingredients over crumbs.
Drizzle milk over this.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat thoroughly.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda. Add to shortening mixture; mix well.
Blend in oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix all together and line pie pan.

title: greek chicken
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, in small bowl with fork, mix Feta cheese, lemon juice and oregano until smooth. On work surface, with meat mallet or dull edge of French knife, pound each chicken breast half to 1/2-inch thickness. With knife or small metal spatula, spread cheese mixture over each breast half to within 1/2-inch of edge. Fold chicken breasts crosswise in half to enclose filling; secure with toothpick. On sheet of waxed paper, mix salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon flour; use to coat chicken. In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot olive or salad oil, cook chicken until golden brown on both sides, turning once.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place meat, onion, water and salt in large soup kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove meat from broth and cube. Remove fat.
Replace meat in broth; add tomatoes, celery, cabbage, potatoes and carrots.
Simmer 1/2 hour to an hour.
Other vegetables may be used.
If canned or leftover vegetables used, add 1/2 hour before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add refried beans and taco seasoning.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sour cream, green taco sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: karen's enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Mix in beans, picante sauce and jalapenos. Prepare tortillas per package instructions. Divide beef mixture between the 10 tortillas. Roll tortillas and place in a 13x9 baking dish. top rolled tortillas with taco sauce, then sprinkle with shredded cheddar cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees or until heated thoroughly. Yields 5 servings.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Wash eggplant; boil for about 10 minutes.
Cut in half lengthwise; scoop out pulp to make 2 shells about 1-inch thick. Reserve pulp.
Sprinkle shells with salt.
Cook bacon slightly; add mushrooms and onion.
Cook over low heat for about 10 minutes, or until soft and lightly browned.
Add soft bread crumbs, cucumber, horseradish, chili sauce, seasonings and chopped eggplant pulp.
Fill the eggplant shells with the mixture. Sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Place in a shallow baking dish containing a little.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for about 35 minutes, or until tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Combine peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a hard boil over high heat.
Remove and set aside for 20 minutes.
Return to heat. Bring to a full rolling boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Add liquid pectin and food coloring.
Stir, skim off foam and pour into hot jars.
Cover with thin layer of paraffin wax.

title: overnight brunch eggs
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Break eggs; add milk, mustard and salt.
Add bread, cheese and sausage.

title: colcannon
directions: Cover potatoes with water in large Dutch oven or pot; boil until tender, about 20 minutes.
While potatoes cook, trim and slice cabbage.
Add to pan, adding more water as necessary. Combine onion and evaporated milk in medium saucepan and simmer over medium heat until onion is soft, about 15 minutes.
When potatoes and cabbage are tender, drain water from pan.
Spoon potatoes into bowl and mash.
Add cabbage and milk-onion mixture; season with pepper to taste and serve.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: old time pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
except
cucumbers
in
a saucepan and bring to a
boil.
Drop
clean whole small cucumbers in vinegar and heat.
Simmer for a few minutes but do not boil. Remove
cucumbers and
place
in
clean
jars.
Return vinegar to boil and pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare soup as stated on can; bring to boil.
Add rice and tuna with water, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Add layer of sliced cheese.
Pour other half over cheese and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until hot and cheese bubbles.

title: pickled beets(canned)
directions: Mix syrup ingredients and boil for 10 minutes before adding to beets.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat the eggs, flour and the sugar together; add the ground pecans, then top with the pecan halves and bake for 55 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: cranberry nut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, lemon pudding mix and baking soda together.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Add cranberries, sprinkled with 3 tablespoons powdered sugar, and nuts, sprinkled with flour.
Pour in large tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: john's crab stew
directions: Place crab meat in water.
Bring to a boil.
Add other ingredients and let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add onion and celery, stirring constantly. Add chicken stock, potatoes and garlic salt.
Cook until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Put in blender. Add other ingredients. Stir to blend. Serve hot or very cold. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lime-pineapple jello with topping
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When completely dissolved, add ginger ale and pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Refrigerate until firmly set.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers as directed on package.
Cool.
Put one layer in punch bowl, pressing down into bowl to fit bottom.
Pour 1 package pudding mix, prepared according to directions.
Let set until cool.
Add half of remaining ingredients.
Add second cake layer and second package of pudding mix.
Let set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Finish with whipped topping.
Decorate with sliced peaches and whole strawberries.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix gelatin and 2 cups water and set aside.
Combine jello, 2 1/2 cups water and sugar in cooker.
Bring to boil.
Mix 2 mixtures together; add 1 cup cold water.
Pour into pan/dish and let set until it jells.
Then refrigerate until chilled.
Cut into squares.

title: chili-cheese corn bread
directions: Chop pepperoni.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, measure flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With wire whisk, beat eggs, milk, oil and sour cream until smooth.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture.
Stir in pepperoni, cheese, onion and green chilies.
Spoon batter into pan. Bake for 45 minutes, or until golden brown and toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Makes 14 servings.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients with small amount of bacon drippings in pan.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine beans, onions and sauce in casserole, mixing well.
Top with bacon.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well with a fork.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked ham with pineapple glaze
directions: Combine ingredients to make a smooth paste.
Place ham in baking dish on rack.
Smooth glaze over.
Bake at 400° for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: shipwreck
directions: In a buttered casserole dish, put layers of onions, potatoes, ground beef, celery and kidney beans, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper.
Pour soup over top.
Cover and bake 2 hours in 350° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; put into a Pyrex baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dilled green beans
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, cook broth, onion, green pepper and dill seed for several minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Add beans.
Cook, covered, 5 to 8 minutes.

title: great pumpkin dessert
directions: In mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar and pumpkin pie spice.
Pour into a 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Drizzle with melted butter, then sprinkle walnuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.

title: pork marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients together and marinate a pork loin roast or pork tenderloins.
Bake roast at 350° and baste sauce over the top of the roast.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a baking dish.
Crush crackers and brown in the oleo.
Put browned crackers on top of chicken mixture and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, oatmeal, soda and salt together and add to first mixture.
Add raisins and juice.
Drop from teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pot, cook just until done (but not mushy) in enough water to cover them.
Add small amount of parsley flakes, salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 can of cream of celery soup.
Add cheese and cut heat off.
Stir frequently until all the cheese is melted.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Cook until it spins a thread and flies away.
Add peanuts and cook until slightly brown. Remove from fire.
Add soda.
Stir very quickly and pour in greased sheet.
Can add more peanuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, salt, pepper, onions and bouillon cubes.
Take chicken off bone and set aside.
Save 5 cups broth and mix margarine with it and stuffing mix.
Pour stuffing mix in pan, sprinkle chicken over stuffing mix and mix lightly until moist. Pour some more broth over top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and beat well together.
Bake for 1 hour in a Bundt pan at 350° or less according to your stove oven.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Bring to boil the first 3 ingredients, then boil for 8 minutes more, stirring all the time.
Add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
