Stir until well blended.
Add vanilla and blend.
Add chopped nuts.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Mix dry ingredients, then add to sugar and oil.
Add carrots and blend well.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Blend well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch (lightly greased) pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: family favorite
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Heat soups with milk, stirring until smooth.
Do not add water to soup.
Remove from heat.
Stir in uncooked rice and pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over top. Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until chicken is done.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil sugar and molasses 5 minutes (no longer).
Remove from heat.
Add butter and soda.
Stir mixture until it becomes foamy. Pour over popcorn.
Mix well.
Keep hands slightly buttered; form into balls.

title: green chile chicken
directions: In medium skillet, over medium-high heat, cook chicken, onion and garlic in oil until chicken is no longer pink.
Add salsa, chiles and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or in tortillas.
Top with sour cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: upside-down strawberry meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites with vinegar and salt to soft peaks. Gradually add the 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla, beating to stiff peaks.
Spread on bottom and sides of baked pastry shell.
Bake in 325° oven for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: mary talley's rolls
directions: Add eggs and 4 cups of flour to mixture.
Then add the rest of the flour 1 cup at a time mixing well.
Do not knead.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate or can use immediately.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Cook carrots until done.
Alternate layer of sauce.
Let set for 6 to 8 hours and enjoy.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Precook onion and zucchini for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix cooked onion and zucchini with sour cream and cream soup.
Use 1/2 of stuffing in bottom of baking dish.
Spread zucchini mixture over the stuffing.
Cover with rest of stuffing and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake carob cookies
directions: Combine first four ingredients and bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly. Place on waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: country fried steak
directions: In plastic bag or bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper. Place buttermilk in shallow pan or bowl. Coat steaks with flour mix, then dip into buttermilk and coat with cracker crumbs.

title: baked ham, cooked with brown sugar and pineapple
directions: Take a shank ham portion.
Get a large broiler pan.
Take a sort of aluminum foil bowl.
Put the ham in.
Take a long, sharp knife and punch holes deeply in the ham.
Prepare the brown sugar and pineapple.
Mix the juice with 3 tablespoons of brown sugar in a small boiler.
Stir well while heating on low.

title: bacon-onion hors d'oeuvres
directions: Measurements depend on amount desired.

title: microwave pecan brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir together corn syrup and sugar.
Cook on 100 percent power for 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts. Cook on 100 percent power for 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup and blend well.
Cook on 100 percent power for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.
Keep in a tight container.

title: pizza pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat.
Mix pizza sauce, garlic and oregano and pour over hamburger.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add on top the Mozzarella cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, oil and flour.
Pour mixture on top of Mozzarella cheese.
Top with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fig spice cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, pudding mix, water and oil.
Beat well. Fold in figs and nuts last.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Stays moist and freezes well.

title: sweet bread(scandinavian)
directions: Melt butter in hot milk and set aside.
Add yeast to cool milk and add sugar, cardamom, salt and eggs.
Combine the two sets of liquids in a large bowl. Add approximately 8 cups flour.
Knead into a rather stiff dough.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning divide the dough into 6 pieces.
Roll out into strips, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Braid 3 strips together into a loaf.

Set on a greased flat pan or cookie sheet; let dough rise lightly, about 1 hour. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes (until nicely browned). Remove from oven; brush top with sugar melted in a little hot coffee. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and 7-Up together. Add eggs, one at a time. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour. Mix 1 cup powdered sugar and juice of 1 lemon. Pour over cake while still warm to make glaze.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Coat large (10-inch) pan or skillet with Pam.
Heat pan, brown cubed beef; drain off excess fat by pouring pan contents through a colander.
Return beef cubes to pan.
Season lightly with Lawry's seasoned salt.
Add French onion soup (2 cans), water and Burgundy.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours; stir occasionally. Uncover and cook down to desired thickness.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Combine and cook all but tortillas for about 15 minutes.
Fry tortillas in oil in skillet.

title: new orleans praline bacon
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
On rack of a large broiler pan, arrange bacon slices in one layer and cook in middle of oven 10 minutes or until it just begins to turn golden.
In a small bowl, mix together sugar and chili powder.
Remove pan from oven and sprinkle bacon with sugar mixture and top with pecans.
Return to oven and cool for as long as you desire.
Freezes well for future reheating.	Do not count on any leftovers.	I usually make a lot of the sugar - chili powder mix with the chopped pecans mixed in and store in zip-lock in the freezer.
Then it is handy for quick fixing.
Do not overcook, or sugar will blacken.

title: "cabbage casserole"
directions: Spread chopped cabbage in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice over chopped cabbage.
Add meat and onion. Heat tomato soup and water to boiling.
Pour over cabbage and meat.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated oven at 350° for one
hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook meat and drain; butter 9 x 13 pan. Put in layer of white bread cubes or hash browns. Put meat on top of bread or hash browns. Add layer of Cheddar cheese. Pour over the mixture: 4 beaten eggs, 1 teaspoon salt and 2 cups milk. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 hour (covered). Add onion and green peppers to top. Also add microwaved Cheez Whiz on top. Also can add sour cream and salsa for topping.

title: icebox coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions on the box.
Add frozen coconut and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lunchtime pizza
directions: Mix together until a firm dough forms.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and divide into 4 equal pieces.
Using a floured rolling pin, roll each piece into a 7 to 8-inch circle.
Place on greased baking sheet.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together with a wire whip and chill at least 4 hours.

title: cottage cheese
directions: Heat sour milk to a temperature of about 98° and let stand until it is uniformly warm throughout and the curd separates from the whey.
Drain the whey off; add melted butter or cream, salt and pepper and serve while fresh.
It may be flavored with pimentos, chopped olives or chopped nuts.
The curd and whey may be separated by pouring boiling water over the milk.

title: potato omelet
directions: Well grease a 12 X 12 pan. Put tater tots in pan. Mix eggs and milk and pour over tatet tots. Top with crumbled bacon. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Top with grated cheese while still hot.

title: chili bean pie
directions: In medium size casserole dish put 1/2 can chili and beans. Chop onions and add to layer of chili and beans.
Add layer of crushed corn chips.
Add half of grated cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used. Bake at 350° until onions are done.

title: basic white sauce
directions: Slowly melt margarine.
Add flour and salt.
Pour in milk gradually, stir until thickens.
May add onions and mushrooms to margarine before adding flour.
After mixture thickens, add Worcestershire sauce.

title: cream nuts
directions: Combine sugar and sour cream in a pan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until medium soft-ball forms when dipped in water.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts. Stir until light sugar coating.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it is almost firm.

title: molasses custard tart
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, molasses and butter.
Put in unbaked tart shells.
Makes 6 small tarts.
Bake at 325° to 350° until appears done as the consistency of a chess pie.

title: strawberry, rhubarb pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with half the pastry.
Combine rhubarb, strawberries, sugar, salt, tapioca and cinnamon and pour mixture into pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with a lattice top crust. Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 45 minutes.

title: ramen skillet
directions: Brown ground beef.
Sprinkle seasoning packets on cooking ground beef.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce, salsa and onion. Stir well, then add broken Ramen noodles.
Stir in just a little. Cover and simmer until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally. When noodles are done, stir until all is combined.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Cover, just long enough to melt.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bread and butter pickles(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice, until cucumber is crisp-tender and onion is translucent.
Ladle into a glass jar (rinsed with hot water to prevent cracking).
Cover; cool slightly and refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake.

title: "honeybee cookies"
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, brown sugar, honey and egg in a medium bowl on medium speed, scraping bowl constantly, until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop the dough by teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set and light brown around edges (surfaces of cookies will appear shiny), 7 to 9 minutes.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet, then remove from cookie sheet with metal spatula onto a wire rack.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: roquefort grapes
directions: Toast walnuts on a baking sheet in a preheated 275° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool and chop coarsely.
In the bowl of an electric mixer, combine cream cheese, Roquefort and cream and beat until smooth.
Drop grapes into the cheese mixture and gently stir by hand to coat them.
Then roll the coated grapes in the chopped walnuts and put on a sheet pan lined with wax paper.
Chil until ready to serve.

title: 2-chocolate marble bars
directions: Grease loaf pan and line with plastic wrap.
Leave extra over edges.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil 2 minutes. Add pecans, oatmeal and vanilla flavoring.
Stir well and drop on wax paper to cool.

title: sticky buns
directions: Place pecans on bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Place frozen dough rolls on top of pecans.
Sprinkle with pudding mix and cinnamon.
Melt oleo and brown sugar and drizzle over rolls. Cover with a light cloth and allow to rise overnight (or 6 to 8 hours).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Invert pan over large platter or tray and allow to drip for a few minutes, then remove pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Cook ground beef; add sauces, mushrooms and bell pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
In a large baking dish, place a layer of noodles, beef mixture and cheeses. Repeat layers until all are used up.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, eggs, white sugar and vanilla.
Add soda, salt, flour and chocolate chips.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes large batch.

title: pretzel rounds
directions: Lay round pretzels on foil.
Melt square almond bark or white chocolate in microwave; dip by spoon and fill pretzels.
Top with M&M's or for Easter, top with small jelly bean.

title: cherry  cream  cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy. Add sugar and vanilla and beat until blended. Fold in cool whip. Pour in crust and put 1 or 2 cans cherry pie filling over the top. Refrigerate.

title: huckleberry pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add milk and beat. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Finally, add huckleberries.
Do not beat more than necessary after adding dry mixture.
Bake in greased pan 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Mix until blended. Stir in crab meat, cheese and onions.
Pour in a 9-inch pie plate (no crust).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: festive sweet potatoes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and put them in a greased pan or casserole dish.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
When well mixed, sprinkle on top of potatoes and bake at 375° about 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: berry special breakfast drink
directions: Blend ingredients in blender until smooth.

title: "not your mom's" bread pudding
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes. Spread in a shallow baking pan. Cover loosely and let dry overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat soups, water and margarine until margarine melts.
Put rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place chicken on top of rice. Pour soups over chicken and rice.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: fresh fruit salad(sugar-free; good for dieters)
directions: Cut fruit into bite size pieces.
Add juice for liquid. Sweeten to taste with your favorite non-sugar sweetener.

title: provencal dressing
directions: Put mustard, lemon juice, garlic and yogurt in a glass bowl. Slowly whisk olive oil in and whisk thoroughly until the mixture thickens.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours to allow flavors to blend. Especially good with salads containing meat.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated sharp cheese on top and bake another 15 minutes.

title: sharon's famous oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Place oatmeal in blender or food processor and blend until a fine powder.
Combine oatmeal, flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well and set aside.
Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix butter mixture with flour mixture until completely combined.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by heaping tablespoon on an ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes (12 minutes for soft and 15 minutes for crisp).

title: toffee nut bar
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and butter.
Pat this into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: bows and brie
directions: Saute garlic, crushed, in olive oil.
Add chopped tomatoes. Stir in Brie; pour bow ties into tomato mixture.
Add pine nuts, basil, salt and pepper.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in 1 tablespoon salt and water for 2 hours. Bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar and celery seed; pour over cucumbers.
Will keep in refrigerator for up to 6 months.

title: eggless spice cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together with a fork.
Add oil, vinegar and water.
Stir quickly, batter will be thin.
Add raisins if desired. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle brown sugar over bottom of a 10-inch baking dish or pie plate.
Stir together the flour, granulated sugar and cinnamon; stir in egg until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Pour melted butter over top. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: delicious dip
directions: Using an electric mixer, combine ingredients well and chill. Delicious with potato chips or Fritos.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix together flour, soda and salt; add to cereal.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Mix into dry ingredients.
Mix in buttermilk.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chili citrus chicken
directions: In small dish, mix together chili powder, cumin, garlic salt and cayenne pepper. Rub mixture on each chicken breast half. In frypan, place oil and heat to medium temperature. Add chicken and cook, turning, about 12 minutes or until chicken is brown and fork can be inserted in chicken with ease. Remove chicken to warm platter and keep warm.

title: crisscross cookies
directions: Mix shortening, egg and sugar together.
Stir in milk and lemon extract.
Sift flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda together; stir in creamed mixture.
Add raisins.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Put on ungreased baking sheet; flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour in baking dish.
Mix next 4 ingredients together and sprinkle over batter mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: green flash
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Fill tall glasses with ice and pour vodka mixture over ice.
Garnish with lime slices and enjoy.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread bean mixture in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed. Serve with chips.
Yields 8 cups.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in the buttermilk.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in yeast/buttermilk mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 3 to 4 times.
Roll to a 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Lightly brush tops with melted butter.
Yield:
about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat; add other ingredients and place in a pie shell.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut butter into the mixture to make coarse crumbs.
In another bowl, combine molasses, egg and 3/4 cup hot water.
Stir soda into 1/4 cup hot water.
Immediately fold into molasses mixture.
Pour half of the molasses mixture into pie shell.
Top with half of crumbs, all but 1/4 cup of remaining molasses mixture in a spiral over top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until nicely browned and center appears firm when pie plate is gently shaken.
Cool to room temperature before cutting.

title: chocolate peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa in a large saucepan. Stir this often as you bring the mixture to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla; mix quickly.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and let them cool.
Kids love them!!!

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic powder.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
If sherry is used, double the amount of flour and add sherry with soup.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: sue's hominy pudding
directions: Mix hominy with eggs, milk, sugar, salt and sliced fruit. Place in a buttered, deep baking dish and sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Set dish in a pan with 1/2 cup of water (the water should come halfway up sides of dish).
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 45 minutes.
(Test after 45 minutes with knife edge.
If knife comes out clean, pudding is done.
The center will set as pudding cools.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well with mixer.
Add flour, salt, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put marshmallow cream on while warm.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Brown meat slowly in small amount of hot oil.
Sprinkle meat with salt.	Combine vinegar, oil, catsup, soy sauce, worcestershire, rosemary, garlic powder and mustard; pour over roast.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Remove roast and heat sauce to skim excess fat; spoon sauce over meat.
Serves 6 to 8. Delicious with mashed potatoes.

title: apea cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and add sugar, lard and margarine. Work with hands and then add sour milk. Work it like you do pie dough.
Then roll in batter cake.

title: sweet potato pear bake
directions: 1. Drain pears, reserve 2 Tbsp. of juice (discard remaining juice or save for another use).

title: strawberry kiwi tart
directions: You can use any fresh fruit, not frozen.

title: easy no-fail pot roast
directions: Line pan with heavy-duty foil, large enough to wrap around roast.
Place roast in foil and sprinkle top with 2 to 3 tablespoons steak sauce.
Add mushroom soup and onion soup.
Seal foil around roast and bake at 325° for 1 hour a pound.
Serve with rice.
Different types of creamed soup will result in a variety of gravies.

title: david's perfect pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in bowl.
Stir in sugar, oil, egg and flour.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise in warm place for 20 minutes.
Punch dough down.
Spread into 2 nonstick pizza pans.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Top with your favorite pizza toppings.
Bake until cheese is lightly browned.
Yields 2 pizza crusts.

title: frozen passion
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Proceed according to the operating instructions for freezer.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: diabetic banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients.
Add shortening, mashed bananas and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in oats.
Drop cookies by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes approximately 32 cookies.

title: zucchini bisque
directions: Simmer the onion, zucchini and chicken stock for 15 minutes.

title: baked fudge
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored; add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Add melted butter and stir in remaining ingredients with the exception of the whipped cream.
Pour into 12 x 8-inch pan.
Set pan in a larger pan of water and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes, until set, like custard.
Serve warm with whipped cream. A chocolate lover's dream!

title: mrs. smearly's potato rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine potatoes, shortening, sugar, salt and warm milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and egg. Stir in flour.
Knead on floured board until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease all sides.
Cover and let rise 1 hour; punch down.
Roll in a ball and let rest for 10 minutes. Roll out on floured board; shape into rolls or cut.
Place on greased pan and let rest 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pecans and coconut in bottom of pan. Mix up cake mix according to the directions on the box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt oleo and cream cheese in microwave.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Pour into cake mix, swirl, being careful not to stir up nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown the hamburger and chopped onion.
Add the enchilada sauce, mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, Ortega peppers, ripe olives and milk.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the corn tortillas, cubed.
Mix and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients. Add elbow macaroni, celery, green peppers and onion. Toss to coat. Cover and chill. Makes 5 cups.

title: fresh tomato casserole
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add seasonings.
Saute celery, pepper and onion until crispy tender.
(This may be done ahead of time.)
Add stuffing and toss.
Add tomatoes and sugar; toss gently.
Cover and cook until tomatoes are hot yet firm, 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Line baking sheet with foil and coat well with vegetable cooking spray. Scrub potatoes well and cut into 1/2-inch thick strips. In a large bowl toss potatoes with oil, sugar, salt and cayenne pepper. Spread on baking sheet in one layer. Bake for 30 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: hermits
directions: Cream butter in a bowl.
Add all other ingredients, except flour.
Mix well, then add flour, gradually, until well mixed. Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Saute onions in 1/4 cup of bacon drippings.
Add sugar, salt, garlic powder, dry mustard and vinegar.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Mix this with all the beans (drain the butter, lima and kidney beans but not the baked beans) and the molasses in crock-pot.
Cook on low 5 or 6 hours.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Combine.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips.
tags: frozen white Shoe Peg corn kernels

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth, then all the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer in the order listed.
Bake for 1 hour.
Good served warm or cold.

title: cauliflower mashed potatoes
directions: Cook the cauliflower until firm, yet tender. Coarsely mash cauliflower with potato masher.
Add the sour cream, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in last.
Bake until a toothpick comes out clean.
Bake at 350°.

title: sour cream and hamburger layered casserole
directions: Cook ground beef in melted butter in a large skillet over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain well.
Add tomato sauce and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Transfer meat mixture to a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese and sour cream at low speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Add green onions, stirring gently to combine.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over meat mixture.
Top with
noodles.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: million dollar spaghetti(casserole)
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Saute beef in butter until brown. (If too fatty, drain off.)
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Remove from heat. Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, scallions and green pepper.
In a square 2-quart casserole, spread 1/2 of the spaghetti and cover with cheese mixture. Add remainder of spaghetti and pour melted butter over spaghetti (optional).
Spread tomato/meat sauce over top and chill.
Remove from refrigerator 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Especially good served with green salad and French bread.
Serves 6.

title: low-fat, low sodium biscuits(variation:  old fashioned biscuits)
directions: Fix two 8-inch cake pans with enough safflower oil to dip biscuits in.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, soda and baking powder. In another bowl, cream butter and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix in dry ingredients and chocolates. Can add 3 cups chopped nuts, if desired. Roll into balls and place 2-inches apart on a cookie sheet. Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Combine chunky peanut butter, chocolate syrup and milk in a bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: mom's beer bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Brush top with butter while hot.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Cook noodles-drain-rinse-drain again.
In large bowl, stir together soups, Parmesan cheese garlic powder, sour cream and chopped onion.
Add turkey.
In a 9 X 13 inch casserole/cake pan, layer 1/3 of cooked noodles, spread with 1/3 of turkey mixture, sprinkle with 1/3 of shredded cheese.
Repeat 2 times.
Save cheese to sprinkle on before serving.
Bake at 350° for 45-60 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese, let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cap'n crunch candy
directions: Melt white chocolate.
Mix together all other ingredients. Mix chocolate with the other ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan or drizzle chocolate over other ingredients in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Chill until firm.
Break or cut into pieces or squares.

title: surprise pound cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add water to juice to make a cup.
Add to batter, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oleo and crackers; mix well. Spread in greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix oleo and crushed crackers together.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Press into slightly greased pizza pan. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: Blend together flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda and salt. Add enough margarine to hold mixture together. Press 1/2 of mixture into a greased 9 X 13 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over first layer. Blend caramel with 2 Tbsp. flour and spoon over chips and nuts. Sprinkle the other 1/2 of crumb mixture on top. Bake 20 minutes or more. Cool completely or chill before cutting.

title: good old green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen beans according to package directions; drain. Combine beans, milk, soup and pepper.
Add 1/2 can onions; pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave, covered, 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with 1/2 can onions and pimiento; bake 5 minutes longer or microwave, uncovered, on High 1 minute, then let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients, topping with the combined mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Sprinkle the cheese on top of the dressing and chill.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Line cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Heat butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Add pecans and stir together.
Spoon out onto graham crackers. Bake 10 minutes in 300° oven.
Cool before taking out of cookie sheet.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together thoroughly the first 3 ingredients.
Sift the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together and stir into first mixture. Chill dough. Roll into small balls.
Roll balls in a mixture of the sugar and cinnamon.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400° until lightly browned, but still soft.
These puff up at first and then flatten out with crinkled tops.
Makes about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: skillet supper
directions: Place cabbage pieces in skillet.
Add carrots, potatoes and meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 2 cups of water over all. Place lid on skillet.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: stephanie's mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine onion, Rot-tel tomatoes, soup (no water added), chicken, Velveeta (cubed) and Doritos (crushed).
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Microwave 5 to 6 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.

title: garbanzo spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onion, in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into bowl and add chopped onion.
Refrigerate until ready to serve on bread or crackers.

title: gouda zucchini
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter in a large skillet. Add mushrooms. Salt and pepper to taste.
Lay zucchini slices on top. Add pimento.
Cover skillet and cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Lay cheese slices over top. Cover skillet until cheese melts.
Leftovers are good.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange sherbet
directions: In small saucepan sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup orange juice. Cook over low heat; stir constantly until gelatin dissolves. Remove from heat; stir in balance of orange juice, lemon juice, rind and Sweet 'N Low.
Chill until syrupy.
In small bowl combine dry milk and water.
Beat at high speed until peaks.
Gently stir in gelatin mix.
Blend well.
Pour in shallow pan.
Freeze until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: block party beans
directions: In large dutch oven brown beef over medium high heat.
Drain fat.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste, and ketchup.
Simmer 15-20min.
Spoon into large kettle or roaster.
Add all remaining ingredients; stir well. Bake uncovered 350° 1 hour. Yields 25 servings.

title: garden salad
directions: Stir and refrigerate for later use.

title: pink bride punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Dissolve Kool-Aid in cold water. Add sugar; mix well. Add pineapple juice. Add sherbet and 7-Up when ready to serve.

title: low-calorie spinach lasagna
directions: Brown chopped meat, drain and add to spaghetti sauce.

title: pineapple delight salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add the remaining ingredients.
The horseradish is important in this recipe.
Do not omit.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and spread bread slices with butter or margarine.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage until brown, stirring to crumble; drain well. Spoon over bread slice; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half or milk and salt.
Mix well and pour over cheese. Cover casserole and chill overnight.

title: stew(6 hours)
directions: *You can use 3 tablespoons flour or cornstarch in place of tapioca.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and celery in butter.
Mix together all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350° just until bubbly.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In a large bowl, thaw strawberries and add eggs and oil.
Mix well.
In another bowl, sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar together.
Add strawberry mixture to flour mixture.
Add pecans, if desired, and mix well.
Pour into two buttered and floured loaf pans; bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted margarine together and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.
Cream sugar and cream cheese together and pour over crust.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over cream cheese mixture.
Mix 2 packages of Dream Whip according to directions on box and spread over nuts.
Refrigerate for 2 hours until Dream Whip sets.
Cover with cherry or blueberry pie filling and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: steamed veggies with rice(serves 4)
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart saucepan, bring 1 1/2 cups water and salt to a boil. Add rice.
Cover with tight fitting lid. Bring mixture to a boil, then remove pan from heat. Let stand 30 minutes.
Do not lift the lid during this time.

title: stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Cut sweet potatoes in half.
Scoop out potatoes, leaving thick shells.
Mash potatoes with other ingredients.
Refill shells. Heat at 350° for 10 minutes.
Fat free.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Mix hard to remove lumps. Makes two (1-quart) cans or one (3-pound) Crisco can.
Steam 1 hour for 1-quart can and 3 hours for 3-pound can.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 370° oven for approximately 35 minutes or until lightly brown using a large rectangle pan.
Refrigerate leftovers.
This freezes well.

title: rose's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onion and other ingredients.
Simmer until thick, stirring often, about 2 to 3 hours.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into 1/8-inch slices without paring.
Slice the onions likewise.
Cut green peppers into fine bits.
Mix the salt through the combined cucumbers, onions and green peppers. Place a weighted lid on them and let stand 3 hours.
Drain and set aside.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Open
chilies and squeeze juice into the refried beans. Mix with
package taco seasoning.
Spread bean mixture on platter.
Mix other half of package seasoning into sour cream. Spread
sour
cream over beans.
Arrange chilies, then olives, then
tomatoes
and
onion
over sour cream.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over
dish
right
before
serving.
If
you
take this somewhere,
keep cheese in separate container, then add before serving.
Serve with Doritos.

title: petite pecan pies
directions: Divide into walnut size balls and shape into muffin tin.

title: tomato zucchini stew
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, brown and crumble sausage.
Add celery and cook for 15 minutes; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato juice, zucchini and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add corn and peppers.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir into stew.
Bring to a boil and cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lime salad
directions: Chop marshmallows and dissolve marshmallows and jello in hot water.
Add juice from pineapple.
Chill until syrupy.
Combine cream cheese and pineapple; add nuts.
Mix in jello mixture.
Put in mold.
Serves 11 to 12.

title: chicken in a skillet
directions: Coat chicken in flour, then brown in skillet in oil.
Peel and slice carrot and lay slices over the chicken pieces.
Mix soup and seasoning.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and cook slowly over medium heat for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Put cereal in large bowl and pour peanut butter mixture over it.
Mix well.
Press into buttered 12 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Allow to cool and cut into bars or small squares.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Bake cake mix according to the directions in a tube or 9 x 13-inch pan. Slice into slices when cool. Layer slices of cake, pineapple, strawberries and pudding until large bowl is full. Spread Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Best if refrigerated for several hours before serving.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container. Add heaping 1/3 cup mix to a full cup of hot water.

title: festival slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, red cabbage, carrot, onion and cashews in a medium bowl; toss gently.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Yield:
8 servings (43 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: creamy salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, pudding and 2 cups water in pan.
Cook to a boil; cook for 5 minutes longer.
Cool and put lid on pan and put in freezer until it congeals, about 1 hour.
Beat in Cool Whip and stir in oranges; place in dish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Pour into two well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes. Remove from pan to cool. May add nuts.

title: summer pasta
directions: In a large serving bowl, mix all ingredients except pasta and cheese. Cook pasta according to package directions.
Toss pasta with tomato mixture. Chill.
Add cheese before serving and toss gently.

title: roast pork tenderloin with vegetables
directions: Salt and generously pepper pork tenderloin.
Mix together lime juice and wine.
Pour over tenderloin.
Marinate in refrigerator for 30 to 45 minutes.
Reserve liquid.
Spray glass roasting pan with olive oil spritzer (or cover bottom of dish with 2 tablespoons olive oil).
Place tenderloin in center of roasting pan.
Place prepared vegetables on both sides of pork. Pour reserved marinade liquid over pork and vegetables.
Sprinkle salt, garlic powder, oregano, paprika and remaining black pepper.
Pour stewed tomatoes over mixture. Drizzle remaining tablespoon of olive oil over vegetables or give vegetables a quick spray of oil with spritzer.
Cover loosely with foil.
Roast in 450° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover for last 20 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: This is best if left in the refrigerator overnight so that it gains some volume.
It is very thin if used as soon as made, but it is still delicious.

title: chicken fried pork chops
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then in crumbs. Brown on both sides in skillet.
Season with salt.
Add water and cover.
Cook over low heat 45 to 60 minutes.
Lift chops occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: angel food-sherbet cake
directions: Slice angel food cake horizontally in middle; separate.
Slice 1-inch pieces of sherbet and place on bottom layer of cake.
Cover all of bottom layer with sherbet.
Place top layer of cake. Refreeze.
Cut wedges and serve.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: italian chicken
directions: Put dressing mix and flour in plastic bag and shake with chicken, one piece at a time.
Melt margarine and mix with lemon juice. Spray baking pan with Pam.
Place chicken breasts in pan. Spoon lemon juice mix over chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add 3/4 cup water and bake 15 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: apple slice
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in Crisco.
Put egg yolk in cup; add enough milk to measure 2/3 cup.
Add to crust mixture, mixing well.
Roll into 11 x 15-inch rectangle.
Place in raised edge cookie sheet.
Cover with crushed corn flakes and apples mixed with the cinnamon and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Roll the rest of the dough for top crust.
Brush top with egg white.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes.
Glaze.

title: microwave soap
directions: Save your broken pieces of bath soap by dropping in a quart jar with lid.
Keep closed.
When full, place soap in bowl in microwave.
Set on Medium power, about 10 minutes.
When soap chips begin to puff up, stir.
Do this several times.
Spray small plastic containers with pan coating.
When soap chips are melted, use a spoon back dipped in water to pat soup firmly down in containers.
Let dry overnight and cut to size if too large.
Let dry a week before use.

title: grinch pudding
directions: Boil water for Jell-O as directed on packages.
Mix both packs of Jell-O with the boiled water.
Stir until dissolved.
Put several ice cubes in and stir until Jell-O begins to thicken. Remove the remaining ice and chill Jell-O in refrigerator until it becomes firmer but not completely set.
Mix in Cool Whip, whatever amount looks good to you.
Mix in drained pineapple tidbits and chopped walnuts and refrigerate for at least 2 more hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together well.
Form into a ball.
Chill.
Top with preserves before serving.

title: polenta(microwave)
directions: Mix together until smooth in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Add 3 cups boiling water; stir well.
Cover with Saran wrap and microwave on High for 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove; stir well.
If too thick, more water may be added.
Put back into microwave for 7 to 10 more minutes on High.
This is done in 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In large bowl mix chocolate chips, peanut butter and marshmallow and stand aside.
In large saucepan melt butter slowly.
Add evaporated milk and sugar; stir continuously to rolling boil for 7 minutes.
Pour over chocolate chip mix.
Add vanilla; stir until blended.
Put in pan and chill.

title: cheddar ball
directions: Bring Cheddar cheese and cream cheese to room temperature. Add milk, green onion, pimento and Worcestershire sauce to cheeses.
Mix well.
Cover after shaping into a ball.
Chill 4 to 24 hours.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until crumbly.
Add half the beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread with pineapple.
Mix 1 cup sugar, butter and coconut.
Add remaining eggs.
Mix well.
Spread over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter; add cocoa and sugar alternating with milk.
Beat to spread.
Blend in vanilla.
Makes 2 cups of frosting.

title: p.b.k. cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use floured hands to mix together all ingredients.
Roll into 1 1/4-inch balls and bake 12 minutes. Remove and immediately push a Hershey's Kiss into the center.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix food coloring and cocoa; set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs to sugar and beat.
Add food coloring mixture and mix well.
Add buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients and beat. Mix well.
Bake in well-greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes (2 pans).

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add undrained
pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill until very thick. Then fold
in
carrots and pecans.	Pour into individual molds or a
1-quart	mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Garnish with additional pineapple if desired.
Makes about 3 cups or 6 side salads.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to lime Jell-O.
Dissolve and add 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Add 1 cup boiling water to lemon Jell-O; dissolve.
Stir in marshmallows.
Let cool and add cream cheese.
Beat until blended. Chill until slightly thickened, then blend in whipped cream, pineapple and salad dressing.
Chill until thick.
Spoon over lime Jell-O and chill until set.
Dissolve raspberry in 1 cup boiling water, then add 3/4 cup cold water.
Let stand until thick, then pour over lime and lemon mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix.
Use an 8 x 8-inch square pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix all prepared ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown cornflakes in butter for topping.
Put first ingredients into baking dish and top with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna and potato chip casserole(microwave)
directions: Place 1/3 of crushed chips in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In medium bowl combine remaining ingredients except chips.
Spread half of tuna mixture over chips.
Top with another 1/3 of chips and remaining tuna.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top.
Microwave at High 4 to 6 minutes or until heated, rotating dish 1/4 turn after half the cooking time.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Pull mushroom stems and wash. Mix all other ingredients. Fill mushroom caps with cream cheese mixture. Broil until brown and bubbly.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in egg; add milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend into first ingredients.
Spread batter in greased 9-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices on top of batter, pressing them slightly into the batter.
Combine sugar substitute and cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Yield: 16 (2 inch) squares.
Carbohydrate 23 g, protein 2 g, fat 4 g, calories 136.
One square = 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange, 1 fruit exchange.

title: banana split
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs and oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and oleo until fluffy, then add vanilla and beat again.
Spread over cracker crumbs.
Cut bananas and put on filling.
Drain pineapple and put over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Add nuts and cherries on top.
Chill overnight.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together; bake in a loaf pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and sugar.
Blend in butter to form a soft dough.
Cover and chill until dough is firm.
Shape into small balls or teaspoonfuls.
Roll in coconut.
Place on ungreased baking sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
(For Christmas, sprinkle with colored sugar.)
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Serve with raw broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, celery and cucumbers.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: In medium-sized bowl, mix cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and ham or beef.
Stir until well mixed and keep in refrigerator until ready to use.
Serve on crackers or mini-rye loaf bread.

title: shrimp paste
directions: Combine shrimp and onion in a food processor or blender.
(If you don't own a food processor, then chop finely for dip.)
Cover and process.
Combine shrimp mixture, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, pepper and salt.
Stir in enough mayonnaise to make of spreading consistency.
Serve with bread or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: betty's zuke bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased bread tins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: golden pie crust
directions: Mix and blend.
Add to flour mixture.
Lift with 2 forks until blended.
Pat into ball and refrigerate at least 15 minutes.
Makes 4 one crust pies or 2 doubles.
Can be frozen and rolled later. Brush top crust with canned cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in sugar, syrup, butter, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers, sugar, vinegar and butter in large pot and mix thoroughly.
Place over high heat and bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in pectin. Bring back to full boil. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Ladle quickly into hot jars to within 1/8-inch of top.
Place covers on, and invert jars for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 jars.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well until creamy.
Ready to eat.
Serve with sliced Granny Smith apples.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put browned hamburger in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and spread over hamburger.
Sprinkle cheese, then Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Cake:
Combine in saucepan and bring to a boil;
1 stick margarine, 1/4 c.
cocoa, shortening, and water.
Combine in a bowl; flour, cinnamon, sugar and soda.
Combine the two mixtures together.
Gradually add buttermilk and eggs.
Pour into sheath pan and bake for 20 minutes in 400 degree oven.

title: barbecue beef sandwich
directions: Saute beef, onion and celery in skillet until lightly browned. Add all other ingredients except buns.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over buns.
Serves 6.

title: better butter beans
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine for about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and chilies, salt, sugar and pepper.
Add butter beans; cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hot sauce
directions: Blend into sauce in blender.
For thick sauce, chill for 2 hours.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: In skillet, saute pecans with butter over low gas flame until lightly browned; drain and set aside.
Combine all remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish; top with pecans.
Bake in a 350° gas oven for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot with assorted crackers, chips or breadsticks.
Yield:
about 4 cups.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix jam, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add soda, hot water, spices and flour.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool; frost with caramel icing.

title: jambalaya
directions: Combine ingredients; bake in greased 2-quart casserole pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: First add all wet ingredients, including zucchini.
Then, add all the dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Leave 1/2 of the catsup.
Form into loaf and place in baking dish.
Pour remaining catsup over loaf and bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter banana squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In small bowl, mix the flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl at medium speed, beat peanut butter and butter until well blended.
Gradually beat in brown sugar and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Beat in banana and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; beat just until blended.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Spread in baking pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until cake pulls away from pan. Cool on wire rack; cut into squares.
Cover with plastic wrap. Serve the next day.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes about 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Layer in casserole.
Put dry crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients. Cook 40 minutes at 225°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cut up potatoes, tomatoes and onions.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil.
Add jello and remove from heat.
Mix well.
Cool.
Combine Cool Whip and buttermilk together.
Mix well.
After pineapple and jello are cooled, mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Cover with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in huge bowl and mash, knead, squeeze, slap and beat.
Form dough into walnut size balls.
Butter bottom of small glass, then dip the glass in granulated sugar and use the glass to smash the balls flat.
You need to butter glass 1 to 2 times but re-dip it in sugar for each ball.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12minutes.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: In a plastic bag, combine the flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Set aside. Skin chicken and rinse. Add chicken to the bag, shaking to coat well. In a skillet, cook chicken in hot oil over medium heat, till lightly browned. Remove chicken from skillet, set aside. Drain fat, reserving 2 tbsp. of the drippings in the skillet. Add mushrooms, onion, green pepper or celery to skillet. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Stir in chicken broth and desired herbs. Bring to boiling. Return chicken to skillet. Bring to a boil again and then reduce heat. Cover and simmer 35 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and vegetables from skillet, set aside. Skim fat from pan. Measure 3/4 cup of the pan juices and return to the skillet. Stir milk into 1 tbsp. of flour. Stir mixture into pan juices. Cook and stir till thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir one minute more. Spoon some of the sauce over chicken. Spoon remaining sauce over hot cooked noodles.

title: homemade lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in the top of a double boiler.
Add very gradually the water or milk.
Stir and cook these ingredients over, not in, hot water for 8 to 12 minutes or until it thickens.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes more.
Stir occasionally. Remove mixture from the heat.
Pour a little of it over 3 beaten egg yolks; beat this and return to mixture in a double boiler. Cook and stir gently, about 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat. Beat in 3 tablespoons butter, 1/3 to 1/2 cup lemon juice (real juice:
1 large or 1 1/2 medium lemons) and 2 teaspoons grated lemon rind.
Cool.
Pour custard into the cold pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix crushed pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine. Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 10 minutes; cool. Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and milk until smooth. Stir in Cool Whip. Spread over crust; refrigerate. Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved. Stir in cold water. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in strawberries. Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Cut into squares. Garnish as desired. Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Brown in iron skillet. Gradually add water.
Beat egg yolks.
Add small amount of milk. Add the balance of milk and salt.
Pour this slowly into the sugar mixture; cook until thick, stirring constantly until thick.
Cool and pour into a baked pie shell.

title: apple cake(good and very easy!)
directions: Peel and dice apples into a bowl.
Add eggs, cooking oil, sugar, vanilla and butter flavor extract.
Mix well.
Stir in flour which has been sifted in baking soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (test with a toothpick).

title: supper strata
directions: Place flour slices of bread on bottom of 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover with 6 process cheese spread slices, ham and remaining process cheese spread slices.
Combine eggs, milk, onion and seasonings.
Pour half of egg and milk mixture over process cheese spread.
Top with remaining bread and egg and milk mixture. Cover.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: burna broed(brown spice cookies)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all of the ingredients, except the granulated sugar.
Knead quickly.
Chill.
Shape the dough into a long roll 1/2-inch wide.
Cut off small pieces of the dough and roll into balls.
Dip the balls into the granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° on a buttered cookie sheet for about 12 minutes.

title: big batch cowboy cookies
directions: Combine margarine, eggs, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well until creamy.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda that has been sifted together.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal and mix.
Add chips or candies or nuts.
Drop by tablespoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for approximately 15 minutes.
Makes 275 to 300 cookies.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well together all ingredients.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle topping on top of potato mixture.

title: english trifle
directions: In large trifle bowl or punch bowl, break angel food cake in small pieces. Mix jello as directed on boxes. When cool pour over cake pieces-slice bananas on top of this-Next layer sliced strawberries. Mix pudding as directed on box, when thick pour over sliced fruit. Spoon cool whip on top and garnish with fresh strawberries and roasted, chopped nuts. Chill in refrigerator. Very pretty as well as cool and refreshing.

title: milk and cinnamon ice
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove cinnamon stick and lemon rind; let mixture cool.
Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks, gradually adding the 1/4 cup sugar while beating.
Gently fold egg whites into milk mixture.
Pour into 2 ice cube trays; freeze 2 to 3 hours (stirring occasionally) until set.
Spoon into sherbet glasses and sprinkle lightly with powdered cinnamon.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese; spread over crust.
Mix both puddings and milk until thickened; spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with the rest of the Cool Whip and chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving. Keep refrigerated.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in a doubled brown paper grocery bag.
In a 2-quart casserole, put the brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt. Bring to a boil on High and microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir, then take out and add baking soda.
Stir well and pour over popcorn. Roll bag up tight and shake.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes, then shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes more and shake.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix oil, dressing and dill weed.
Add crackers and mix well. Stir again every 15 minutes.
Ready in about an hour.
These crackers keep well if sealed in a Ziploc bag.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and red pepper 3 times.
Mix butter with cheese.
Add dry ingredients, using a fork and/or fingers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix
together for 15 minutes the powdered sugar, margarine and eggs.
Crumble the graham crackers into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Drain well
1 large can crushed pineapple and spread on top of egg mixture.
Slice 4 to 5 bananas on top of pineapple. Top
with
1 large Cool Whip.
Cut maraschino cherries in half and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together.
Batter should be kind of stiff.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Turn once.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: deep dish chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, cook celery in margarine until tender.
If using celery soup, add to chicken broth.
Thicken chicken broth with flour and milk.
Do not make it real thick. Pour in chicken, carrots, potatoes and peas.

title: hawaiian sunset cake(3 layer cake)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage stew
directions: Brown sausage and onions together. Drain off grease. Put drained sausage and onions in cooking pot. Add beans, (do not drain beans). Add diced tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste. Cook on low to med. heat for 20 to 30 minutes stirring occasionally.

title: split pea soup
directions: Saute onion and spices in oil for 1 minute.
Add soy sauce, peas and water.
Bring to a boil; simmer 1 hour.
Add potato and celery; cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Make cake as directed. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour over warm cake.
Cook pudding according to package directions.
While still warm, pour over pineapple mixture.
Cool and top with Cool Whip. Must be kept in the refrigerator.

title: healthy chili
directions: Saute turkey, onion and bell pepper in a skillet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Peel tomatoes, chop and add to turkey mixture along with cilantro and chili powder.
Stir, add bouillon cubes and water.
Cover and simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: koch kasse
directions: Cut up cheese and oleo.
Add milk and flour.
Cook over medium heat until melted and the right texture for spreading.
Add caraway seed and pour into container.

title: basic quiche
directions: You can also add broccoli or whatever you desire.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix water and sugar in a pan and bring to a
boil. Boil 4 minutes and let cool.

title: cheese and potato soup
directions: Add broth and other ingredients listed above to pot.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium and cook for 10 minutes.
Check for doneness of potatoes and adjust cooking time to allow for tenderness of potatoes (very soft). 3 cups milk:
Slowly add milk to broth and stir thoroughly until milk/broth is warmed together. 1/3 cup flour, 1 cup cold water:
In separate mixing cup, slowly add flour to COLD water and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture slowly into broth/vegetables, stirring as you add it.
This will thicken the broth. 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese (mild or medium); 1/4 cup (approx.) at a time:
Add cheese to broth, stirring until melted. Repeat until all cheese has been added.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, leaving one bacon strip to place on the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never-fail fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together in 10 x 8-inch utility dish. Drop butter onto sugar mixture in 4 to 5 pieces.
Pour in milk. Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High or until bubbly.
Stir lightly. Thoroughly stir in nuts and vanilla so nuts are evenly distributed. Spread fudge evenly in dish.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Makes approximately 2 dozen pieces.

title: karen's baked fish soupreme
directions: Place fish fillets in a greased baking dish.
If using small shrimp, sprinkle them over fish, and pour soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until fish is tender and flakes.

title: quick stuff turkey breast
directions: Cook Stove Top stuffing as directed.
Cut cheese in strips. Take one slice of turkey breast and add 2 strips of cheese and 1 tablespoon of stuffing to turkey breast; roll up as many as you want and put in large frypan.
Then add gravy.
Let simmer on top of stove for 10 minutes, covered.
Serve with mashed potatoes and your favorite vegetable.

title: golden nut bars
directions: Blend crumbs, pecans, sugar and baking powder.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff, not dry, peaks are formed.
Fold in the crumb mixture, a small amount at a time.
Turn into an ungreased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into bars. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cheese strata
directions: Arrange bread slices in bottom of lightly buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings in medium bowl until well blended.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Beat with mixer the peanut butter, margarine and vanilla real well. Add powdered sugar and mix well. Add nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Roll in small balls and place on cookie sheets lined with waxed paper.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Chop the cabbage and put in salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain and add celery and pepper.
Boil the vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
While hot, pour over cabbage.
Cool and store. Real good on barbecue sandwiches.

title: cheese log
directions: Place cream cheese and Cheddar in bowl until room temperature. Once room temperature, add garlic. Place mixture on wax paper. Form into log. On another piece of wax paper, pour chili seasons. Then roll log through seasoning and wrap up in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
This should make 2 large logs.

title: salmon balls
directions: Pour juice from salmon into measuring cup. Set aside 1/4 cup juice.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together. Form into balls and brown; drain.

title: mock mayonnaise(30 calories per tablespoon)
directions: In covered blender container, at medium speed, blend all ingredients until smooth, scraping the container with a rubber spatula as necessary.
Cover and refrigerate.
Use within 2 weeks. Makes 1 cup.

title: honey fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit and nuts in a large bowl.
Combine orange juice, lemon juice and honey in a small bowl; mix well.
Pour over fruit, tossing gently.
Chill thoroughly.

title: chicken creole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil until limp.
Add chicken, rice, spaghetti sauce and nutmeg.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 45 minutes or bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and put in buttered dish.
Add a few cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at
350° for 40 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots, just until tender, then cool.
Mix all ingredients and pour over carrots.
Marinate 12 hours and drain.

title: cookie brittle
directions: Cream
butter,
salt
and vanilla; add sugar gradually. Add flour and chocolate chips.
Press in pan and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in egg, milk and vanilla.
Fold in flour, baking powder and salt.
Refrigerate overnight.
Knead dough.
Roll out and cut.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 1/2 minutes only.
Cool.

title: cheese rice
directions: Bring water to boiling point.
Add butter, salt and rice. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook covered for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Stir cheese, onion and mustard into hot rice.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cook sugar and cream until mixture reaches the soft ball stage.
Beat until creamy.
If the frosting gets too hard before you get it all on, beat in a little cream.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
In large bowl, pour boiling water over shortening and dissolve.
Add sugar, salt, eggs, flour and dissolved yeast.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk until smooth.
Add salt, pepper, onion and 1 c. cheese.
Add to potatoes. On top, place remaining cheese, bacon bits and bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a large saucepan over low heat.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Remove from heat and slowly stir in sweetened condensed milk.
Add marshmallows and pecans.
Drop by tablespoonful on greased cookie sheets.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: uncooked pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into baked shell.
Let stand 3 hours in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour, pineapple juice, vinegar, dry mustard and soy sauce in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil. Add cocktail franks; reduce heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: easy pudding cake
directions: Prepare chocolate cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
After cool, spread a layer of whipped topping on the cake approximately 1/4-inch thick.

In a bowl, prepare pudding according to manufacturer's instructions and let set for 1 minute. When pudding starts to set, pour over whipped topping and with a toothpick, marble the pudding and whipped topping.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla.
Top with cherries and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese sauce for fish fillets
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls over cooked fish fillets.
Brown under broiler.
Just takes a few seconds.

title: gayle's butter tarts
directions: Put pastry in tart shells.
Mix all ingredients and put in shells.
Bake in 450° oven for 8 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake until thoroughly browned.

title: one day root beer
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in gallon jug and set in sun for four hours.
Chill.
Ready to drink the next day.

title: strawberry surprise(low-fat)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese and Sweet 'N Low liquid; add lite Cool Whip.
Place on cooled pretzel mix. Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water; add berries and place in refrigerator freezer until thickened.
Spoon over Cool Whip with cream cheese mix.

title: nana's christmas pudding and ice cream sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add moist ingredients.
Steam in can* or plum pudding mold for 2 hours in water bath.
Make sure water comes halfway up the can and simmers, but does not boil.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Stir together cake mix and jello.
Add Wesson oil; stir.
Add eggs and stir one at a time.
Let strawberries thaw.
Mash strawberries.
Put 1 cup of strawberries into batter and stir. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: zucchini snack cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar and mix well with oil and vanilla. Combine separately, then add rest of dry ingredients.
Then mix in zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna-swiss pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
To hot rice in saucepan add butter, garlic and 1 slightly beaten egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon rice mixture into ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Press rice mixture firmly across bottom and up sides to form a crust.
Layer 1/2 cup of onions, 1/2 cup cheese and the tuna evenly over rice crust.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: delicious potato doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed, except oil.
Pat out to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a floured doughnut cutter.

title: crab or shrimp casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in rice and cream.
Add seasoning and shrimp.
Boil 5 minutes.
Place in casserole and leave in warm place for several hours to improve taste.
Brown in oven and serve immediately.

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Melt margarine.
Mix sugars and cinnamon in bowl.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Make small balls with bread dough. Dip each ball in melted margarine, then roll in sugar mixture. Put in Bundt pan and put remaining sugars and melted margarine over top.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then cover with foil and bake at 300° for 15 more minutes.
To remove, flip over on serving dish, tray, etc.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: smoky cheese-olive spread
directions: Advance preparation:
Line a 2-cup mold or bowl with clear plastic wrap or foil.
Beat cheeses together until well blended; stir in olives.
Turn into mold.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: sauce for dried beans, turnip greens, etc.
directions: Mix tomatoes, sugar, pepper, salt and vinegar. Simmer about 45 minutes, uncovered. This keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa well.
Make a hole in the center and put in butter and milk.
Microwave 4 to 5 minutes until it bubbles. Remove and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Let cool.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine water, butter and sugar in a saucepan; heat until butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Cool to 120° to 130°. Combine 2 cups flour, salt and yeast in a large mixing bowl; stir well.
Gradually add liquid mixture to flour mixture, beating well at high speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs and beat an additional 2 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually stir in remaining flour, making a soft dough.
Cover and refrigerate up to 3 days; punch dough down and cover if it begins rising out of bowl.

title: sweet dills
directions: Fill 8 quart jars with sliced cucumbers.
Add 2 bunches dill and 3 or 4
garlic cloves.
Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers in jars and seal.
Cold pack 5 to 7 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cook, debone and chop chicken. Place chicken in dish.
Mix soups, broth and vegetables in saucepan over low heat until warm.
Blend together margarine, milk and flour.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: favorite corn sticks
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then add eggs, milk and oil.
Stir until smooth.
Place a well-greased cast-iron corn stick pan in a 425° oven for 3 minutes or until hot.
Spoon batter into pan, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook meat until brown, then add all other ingredients.
Cook about 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon cream cheese rolls
directions: Combine cheese, vanilla and egg well.
Remove crust from bread and flatten.
Spread mixture on slices and roll tightly.
Dip in melted butter and then in cinnamon sugar mixture.
Can be frozen at this point.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In large skillet, saute green pepper and onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer, covered, for 12 to 15 minutes, or until shrimp are firm and pink, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together to break up lumps. Add wet ingredients and mix according to directions on cake mix. Add chocolate chips. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seven layer mexican dip
directions: Layer in a small casserole dish, beginning with beans and ending with cheese.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Serve with tortilla or Fritos chips.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong baking dish with the thicker, meatier portions facing toward the outside of the dish.

title: pumpkin trifle
directions: Mix cake, water and egg.
Bake in 8 inch pan at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes.
When cool, crumble.
Reserve 1/4 cup for garnish.
In bowl, whisk pudding and milk for 2 minutes.
Let stand until becomes soft set.
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
In trifle bowl, layer with cake and pudding mix.
Repeat, ending with pudding. Garnish with reserved cake and nuts.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place in bottom of casserole dish. Mix together soup, poppy seed and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Melt margarine and mix with stack of crackers (crumbled). Sprinkle over soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered chalupa dip
directions: Arrange lettuce around the edge of a large serving platter. Heat refried beans and sausage until hot.
Spread on bottom of platter.
Add Cheddar cheese; sprinkle evenly over beans.
Do same with chopped tomatoes.
Add sour cream (does not have to be spread evenly).
Next, add mashed avocado.
This goes over the sour cream (will extend beyond sour cream or you may surround sour cream). Sprinkle pitted, chopped black olives on top of avocado.
Add large chips around platter for dipping.

title: susan's slaw(easy)
directions: Grate cabbage, pour vinegar and sugar over cabbage.
Mix well. Cover and place in the refrigerator over night.
Drain liquids before serving.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into a loaf.
Place in greased baking dish; cover with Piquant Sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all together. Cook until rice is done.

title: taco goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Simmer until mix is well blended.
Line casserole dish with chips.
Pour meat and other ingredients (mixed well before) into dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, butter, vinegar and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake until firm, about 50 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
Serve garnished with chopped nuts or whipped cream if desired.

title: microwave chocolate chip bars
directions: In small mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate pieces and nuts.
Spread in paper towel-lined 8-inch square dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup chocolate pieces.
Microwave at High 5 to 7 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn every 2 minutes until done.
Cool and cut into bars. Makes 24 bars.

title: funnel cakes
