directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a bowl.
Heat shortening or oil 1-inch deep in a skillet to 375°.
Pour batter (about 1/4 of it at a time) into a funnel, then pour in a circular motion in the hot oil.
Start in the center of the pan.
Do not pour it thick.
Fry each side about 1 1/2 minutes, or until brown. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spinach bisque
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, saute onions in butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt and nutmeg until smooth. Gradually whisk in milk and water. Add cheese; cook and stir over medium heat until melted. Add spinach; cover and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes or until heated through. Serve with oyster crackers. Yield: 5 to 6 servings.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add boiling water; cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter, lemon juice and rind.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cinnamon cheese bars
directions: Press 1 pack crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla and spread on the crescent rolls.
Press on the other pack of rolls.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over top.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon on top.
Mix the cinnamon and sugar together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out onto floured surface and knead about 6 to 8 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Shape into ball and place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 1 hour. Punch dough down; place on lightly floured surface.
Divide into thirds.
Shape each third into a 16-inch rope.
Place rope onto greased baking sheet.
(Do not stretch.)
Braid ropes together, pinching ends to seal.
Cover and let rise in warm place, about 45 minutes or until double in bulk.
Combine egg yolk and 1 tablespoon eggnog.
Gently brush over loaf.
Sprinkle with almonds and 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: crispy honey mustard chicken strips
directions: Line baking sheet with foil.
Spray with no stick cooking spray and set aside.
Slice 4 partially thawed breasts crosswise into 8 - 10 strips.
(4 breasts = 32-40 strips.)
Mix 1/2 c. Grey Poupon honey mustard and 3/4 c. of evaporated milk in shallow bowl.
Pour corn flake crumbs into 1 gallon zipper style plastic bag add 1 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Toss chicken strips in mustard mixture.
Spoon slightly drained strips into crumbs, shake until all strips are well coated.
Place strips on prepared pan, spray tops with non-stick spray.
Bake 500° oven 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for additional 5 minutes.
Place on paper towel to drain. Serve with additional honey mustard.

title: baby pizza snacks
directions: Take English muffins and slice in halves.
Place halves on cookie sheet.
Put 1 tablespoon of pizza sauce on each muffin.
Put your own topping on, then sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is melted or you can cook under broiler.

title: meat loaf
directions: Chop bologna and add to remaining ingredients.
Add catsup last.
Bake in moderate oven until done.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and let
it cool in the broth.
When cool, remove from the bone.
Thaw
broccoli.
Stir undiluted soup to blend.
In a
greased
casserole, layer the chicken, broccoli, soup and Parmesan cheese.
Make
2 layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and oils.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add zucchini. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Grate zucchini.
Do not blend.
May freeze.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put ingredients into blender in order listed.
Blend at blend speed
for	1
minute.
Pour
into 9 or 10-inch pie pan, which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine 1 stick butter and vanilla or graham cracker crumbs. Press into a 7 1/2 x 12-inch pan.

title: shipwreck
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towels to drain; crumble and set aside.
Drain off drippings from skillet.
Brown beef; drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.

title: christmas custard(1 gallon)
directions: Pour 3 1/2 quarts milk into a kettle and place on a low burner on stove.
Never let milk boil.
Heat until, when a spoon is dipped slightly over the top of the milk, a little skin is formed on the spoon.
While waiting for the milk to heat until it forms a skin, break eggs into a bowl or kettle.
Stir (mix) with a spoon until all yolks are mixed thoroughly (do not use mixer).

title: chicken basting
directions: Mix 1 week ahead and store in refrigerator.
Place chicken, skin side up, on medium hot fire (10-inches above charcoal) and baste.
Turn every 15 minutes and baste.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Dump all ingredients in blender and blend on high just a few seconds.
Pour into pie plate. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Layer in order on platter or serving dish.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: hollandaise
directions: In glass container, microwave margarine for 1 minute on High. Add remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High 1 minute; stir every 15 seconds.

title: soft nestle cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and sugar; add eggs and beat mixture until fluffy.
Dissolve baking soda in water, then add to mixture.
Sift flour with salt and gradually add to mixture.
Add chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Mix ingredients 2 minutes at high speed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: east indian rice ring
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Cook onion and almonds until golden. Add raisins; heat until plump.
Add cooked rice.
Mix gently. Press mixture lightly into greased 6 1/2-cup ring mold.
Unmold at once on platter.
Fill with chicken curry.
Top with shredded coconut.

title: pot roast of beef
directions: Rub salt and pepper into beef.
Brown on all sides with vegetable oil in heavy roaster.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Cover tightly.
Simmer until tender, about 3 hours.
Turn occasionally. Vegetables (carrots and potatoes) may be added during last hour of cooking roast.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, onion, pepper and 1 cup nuts. Form a ball; roll in remainder of nuts.
Makes one large or 2 small balls.

title: fried corn
directions: In a heavy cast iron skillet put cooking oil.
Pour corn in bowl and mix with flour, sugar and pepper.
Pour ingredients into skillet that has been preheated with oil.
Reduce heat to low and add about 1/2 of the water.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes or more, stirring occasionally.
When corn begins to stick, add more water.
When ready add butter and a few dashes of paprika and salt to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Cool and crumble.
Cut up broccoli and cauliflower in small pieces.
In large bowl, mix vegetables, onion and cheese together.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over the vegetables and marinate overnight. Sprinkle with bacon before serving.

title: spinach squares
directions: Cook and drain spinach; melt the butter and cheese into spinach.
Mix all other ingredients into a bowl, then mix together.
More cheese can be used, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes, then cut and serve.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients in a double boiler for 1/2 hour.
This would be a wonderful addition to a special ham dinner.
Serves 18 nicely.

title: sweet pretzel nuggets
directions: Place pretzels in a microwave safe bowl.
In a small bowl, combine oil, sugar and cinnamon; pour over pretzels; toss to coat. Microwave, uncovered, on high for 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave 3-4 minutes longer, stirring after each minute or until oil is absorbed.
Cool to room temperature.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread; cut into cubes.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; sprinkle with sausage.
Top with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, pepper and mustard.
Pour over cheese.
Chill 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crab salad casserole
directions: Toss green pepper, onion, celery, crab, eggs and 1/3 cup bread crumbs.
Season mayonnaise with pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Add to vegetable/crab mixture.
Pour into greased casserole and top with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream oleo; sift flour and red pepper together.
Add flour mixture to oleo; mix.
Add grated cheese.
Mix.
Add Rice Krispies and mix.
Make into small balls and flatten with fork. Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix milk and chocolate over low heat until melted.
Add salt, vanilla and nuts.
Don't let it stick to pan.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch pan lined with wax paper and smooth out.
Let it set until hard.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain. Stir margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs into cooked spaghetti.
Spoon mixture into a buttered 9-inch pie plate, pressing to form a "crust". Spread cottage cheese over crust.

title: pear pie
directions: Fill pie shell with sliced pears.
Add sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Crumble together oleo, brown sugar and flour.
Spread over pears and bake in 400° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: aunt shelli's cranberry-pear crisp
directions: Peel, core and thinly slice the pears.
Wash and pick over the cranberries.
Toss the pears and berries in a bowl with sugar and cinnamon.
Spread across the bottom of a 10-inch pie dish. Combine flour, brown sugar, rolled oats and salt in a bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spread evenly over cranberry mixture.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Mix in milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Then add salt, baking powder and flour. Roll out on floured counter and make the dough thick or thin, depending on your taste.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl. Microwave on medium for 3-4 minutes. Stir several times. Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients and mix all together.
Pour into bread pans.
Makes 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it leaves sides of pan.
This freezes very well.
I use for Christmas and Easter dinners.

title: louise's baked grits
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add butter and cheese. Stir until melted.
Add eggs, milk and pepper.
Mix well and pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick, then pour into baked pie shell.
Graham cracker crust is delicious with this pie.

title: pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Unroll dough and press out with your hand on a greased pan.
Top with pizza sauce, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick.
Let cool.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle coconut over filling.
Spread Cool Whip (1/2) over coconut.
Sprinkle coconut again and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Makes 1 pie.

title: vietnam beans
directions: Fry bacon; saute onion in grease (make sure bacon is crisp). Add beans; stir in other ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Crumble and add bacon.
Serves 1 to 4, depending on how much you eat.

title: chili burgers
directions: In glass casserole, saute ground beef, onion and celery 6 to 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Drain off drippings.
Add vinegar, catsup, tomato sauce, mustard, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and chili powder; stir to blend.
Cook, covered, 8 to 10 minutes.
Heat buns wrapped in terry towel 1 minute.
Spoon mixture on heated buns.

title: my mother's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk and then the oil.
Makes about 36 four-inch pancakes.

title: brown bag pickles(for 1 gallon glass jar)
directions: Melt yeast in bottom of glass jar in cool water with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Then add dill weed, few garlic pods and a leaf of horseradish, if you have it.
Bring to boil the water, vinegar and salt.
Let cool.
After cooling, pour over cucumbers that are packed in jar.
Place jar in brown paper bag, close top of bag with a couple of clothespins.
Sun for a couple of days, from there put in icebox.
Eat cold out of jar.
Delicious cold.

title: hearty dinner salad
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed; drain.
Combine all ingredients, including Kraft grated cheese.
Toss lightly.
Chill.

title: popeye's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with assorted vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Cut off and discard small tips of wings.
Cut remaining wing bones apart.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Add half wings; cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and crisp.
Remove; drain well.
Repeat with remaining wings.
Melt butter in saucepan; add hot sauce and vinegar.
Put chicken wings on a warm serving platter.
Cover with butter mixture.
Serve with Blue cheese dressing and celery sticks.

title: grandma power's ole time sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix 1 cup flour and remaining dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix in flour, 1 cup at a time, to right consistency.
Flour board well, roll dough and cut. Sprinkle with sugar or sprinkles.

title: polenta pound cake
directions: Combine in a bowl; toss.
(Can be made ahead, covered and refrigerated up to 4 hours.)
Beat 1 cup heavy or whipping cream to soft peaks; beat in 1 tablespoon confectioners sugar and 1 tablespoon dark rum.
Slice cake into wedges and place on dessert plates.
Serve with berries and cream.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions, combine with other ingredients and boil 30 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place water, oleo, and onion in sauce pan and bring to a boil. Add one package of chopped broccoli and boil for 5 minutes.
Add minute rice to boiled mixture- turn off heat and let stand 10 minutes.
In a bowl, mix 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and 8 oz. jar of cheese whiz.
Mix all ingredients together and place in a 2 qt. casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: starlight cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add margarine, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Combine flour, nuts, brown sugar and oleo.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir once while baking.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs for top.
Using a spoon, press warm crumb mixture in pie plate.
Chill.
Blend cream cheese and sugar and spread over the crust.
Whip the cream and sweeten to taste. Fold pie filling into whipped cream.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle with crumbs.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt the margarine in a casserole.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until it begins to brown.

title: parmesan noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Place in a bowl.
Immediately add remaining ingredients and toss well. Makes 4 servings.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Season to taste.
Remember corned beef is salty.
Mix and pour into greased casserole.
Dot the top with butter and 1/2 cup crumbled potato chips or buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla wafers alternately with milk.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Add noodles, tuna, pimento and parsley. Pour into casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: broccoli and raisin salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar in large bowl; mix well.
Add broccoli, raisins, onion, pecans and bacon; mix well. Chill at least an hour, but better if chilled overnight.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is rough, otherwise just scrub and rinse them.
Cut the potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Put the potatoes in a baking dish, fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs. Bake potatoes for 50 minutes at 425°.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake potatoes for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside. Check with a fork.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring milk and margarine to boil over medium heat.
Add flour all at once, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring constantly, until it is smooth. Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: pepper roll
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing mix
together.
Sprinkle with seasoned pepper.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
remaining
ingredients
and mix well. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart-size casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: drop rolls
directions: Put flour in bowl first.
Then sugar, then yeast.
Next add water, 1 egg, beaten and oil.
Mix together with wooden spoon. Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Fill 1/2 full.
bake 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Pour rest of mixture in Tupperware container and refrigerate.
Stir well each time you use.
No rising necessary.

title: delicious barbecue chicken
directions: Wash and prepare chicken. Sprinkle with allspice on both sides of chicken. Sprinkle with Season-All on both sides of chicken and sprinkle with garlic powder on both sides of chicken. Place on grill until done. Add honey barbecue sauce to chicken on both sides. Let chicken finish cooking on grill. This is a mouth watering recipe you will enjoy!

title: baked beans and meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and bell pepper.
Add seasoning. Pour beans in casserole dish.
Pour other ingredients over them. Bake 30 minutes uncovered at 350° and then 15 minutes, covered. Serve with buttered French bread and green salad.

title: low carb cheeseburger quiche lunch snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger in a heavy skillet; add onion.
Remove and mix in bowl with bacon pieces, breaking up any larger clumps with a fork or pastry mixer until you have a fine mix.
Drain well of any excess grease and press into the bottom of a deep-dish pie pan.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in mixer bowl and whip well.
Pour mixture over beef "crust" and bake 40 to 45 minutes until top is browned and "set".
Cool for 15 to 20 minutes to slice.
This can be packaged in Ziploc or plastic containers for meals quickly microwaved over the next 3 to 5 days. (Does not freeze well, though.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Save syrup and add enough water to the syrup to make 1 cup liquid.
Bring liquid to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid; stir until dissolved.
Add ginger ale. Refrigerate until slightly thick; fold in fruit and marshmallows. Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Beat lemonade concentrate in large bowl about 30 seconds. Spoon in ice cream; beat until blended. Stir in whipped topping until smooth. Place in freezer, if necessary, for mixture to thicken. Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours or overnight.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread mixture on a small serving plate; top with nuts.
Serve with apple wedges.
Yields 6 servings.

title: rabbit with noodles
directions: Boil the rabbit in salted water with the onion until meat falls from bones.
Dice the meat.
Prepare noodles by adding milk and some salt to the eggs.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll the dough out to a thickness of 1/4-inch or less. Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Cover the bottom of a greased (margarine) baking pan with noodles, followed by a layer of rabbit meat.
Continue alternating noodles with meat until both are gone. Pour the broth in which the rabbit was cooked over this and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: wing dings
directions: Singe wings if needed.
Cut off tips and discard.
Divide each wing in half.
Place in single layer or rack in broiler.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, ginger, pepper, water, lemon juice and soy sauce in small saucepan.
Stir constantly until mixture boils; boil 3 minutes.
Brush over chicken.
Cook chicken 40 minutes more and continue turning and basting with remaining mixture.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cook butter and sugar over low heat until bubbly and cool. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.

title: many way meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt.
Shape into 16 meatballs.
In skillet, brown meatballs.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, water and parsley.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes. Stir now and then.
Serves 4.
Very good with other cream soups.

title: cheesy potato souffle
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add yolks, cheese, onion, chives and pepper to potato mixture; stir well.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) and baking powder until stiff peaks form.
Fold into potato mixture.
Spoon into a buttered 1 1/2-quart souffle dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.
Serve immediately. Yield: 6 servings.

title: ella's brownies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan in a 350° oven for around 30 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend for 30 seconds.

title: banana muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix milk, egg and mashed bananas and add to flour mixture with melted margarine. Stir only to mix.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: quick tater tot bake
directions: In a skillet, brown the meat and onion. Drain any fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole. Top with green beans and potatoes.
Combine soup and milk or water.
Pour over the potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with bananas and buttermilk to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.

title: lesby's surprise cake
directions: Sprinkle this mixture over the bottom layer in pan.
Add remaining half of batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and allow to cool 15 minutes in pan.
Turn out of pan and cool completely.

title: turkey fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Cover and chill for 2-3 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs; blend and beat 1 minute. Spread batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in 2 eggs and vanilla.
Set aside 1/2 cup of 10x sugar.
Beat in remaining.
Pour over batter in pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar you set aside (after you bake).

title: falafel and tehina
directions: Drain can of chickpeas.
Mash.
Add next seven ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Taking a spoonful of the mixture at a time, roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Heat oil and deep-fry falafel until browned.
Drain.
Serve hot on a gyro bread or in a pita bread pocket with tehina on top Tehina recipe follows.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
In separate bowl, mix condensed milk and cream cheese together.
Combine until evenly mixed.
Layer cookies, bananas, pudding, etc.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: spinach pesto
directions: In blender or processor, puree all ingredients until smooth. Toss with hot cooked pasta (approximately 1 pound).
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick herb rolls
directions: Spread butter over bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Combine next 3 ingredients and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook, cool and cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix together croutons, broth and butter; line casserole dish.
Add chicken.

title: mexican hot sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine chili sauce, onion, vinegar, salad oil, brown sugar, garlic, salt, dry mustard and Tabasco sauce. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Serve warm or cool.

title: pecan tart
directions: Combine flour, cream cheese and butter.
Form balls about the size of walnuts.
Drop in small muffin tins, making a shell.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine first eight ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinade; coat each piece with crumbs.
Arrange on shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until juices run clear.
Serves 8. Exchanges: 3 1/2 lean meat, 1 starch, 1/4 skim milk and 271 calories.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix well and put on top of cream cheese.
Put rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: chicken wellington with port-currant sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season chicken with salt and pepper. Cook wild rice according to package directions.
Stir in orange peel.
Set aside.
Roll out sheet of puff pastry 1/8-inch thick. Divide pastry into quarters.
Place chicken breast on each pastry quarter.
Spoon 1/4 cup rice on top.
Roll up.
Place seam side down on jelly roll pan.
Beat 2 egg yolks and water.
Brush on dough.
Bake 50 minutes.
Heat currant jelly, mustard, wine and lemon juice.
Serve sauce warm with chicken.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: old-fashioned pone bread
directions: Mix ingredients until moist.
Add enough water to make a smooth mixture (but mixture needs to hold its shape).
Form into pones.
Grease iron skillet and heat.
Place pones into hot skillet.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring water and oleo to a boil.
Take off heat and stir in flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
(Mixture will be smooth.) Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased) and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool!
Cream the cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk.
Add rest of milk.
Add pudding.
Refrigerate pudding for 15 minutes. Spread pudding over crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: Mix egg whites, sugar, salt and water in top of double boiler. Beat over boiling water with sturdy beater or at high speed of electric mixer 7 minutes or until peaks form.
Remove from water; add vanilla.
Beat 1 minute.
Frosts two layers.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs; cut in half.
Mix egg yolks, salad dressing, mustard, salt, pepper and bacon bits together.
Stuff back into white parts.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix ingredients and then add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and mushrooms. Drain off grease.
Add soups, water, rice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes. Transfer mixture to a large covered casserole dish. Bake in a 325° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, evaporated milk, and margarine in a saucepan; let come to a boil.
After bubbles begin, stir constantly for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, pecans, vanilla, raisins, and peanut butter.
Mix until stiff. Pour into 2 greased 9 X 13 pans.
Let cool.
Slice.

title: french meat pie
directions: Mix and cook all together until a little over being raw.
Put in double pie crust and bake at 325° for 40 minutes or more. Makes 2 pies.

title: tuna bacon rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cut pieces of bacon in thirds.
Place small amount of mixture on bacon piece.
Roll up and close with a toothpick.
Broil 10 minutes on each side.

title: sally's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, butter, sugars and peanut butter.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture, blend well.
Mix in oatmeal.
Shape dough into small balls.
Do not flatten.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Spread butter on both sides of the bread. Cut slices in half and set aside. Brown the ground beef. Add onion, celery, prepared mustard and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
In a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, place alternate layers of toast, beef mixture and cheese.
In a small bowl, beat the egg, then stir in the milk, dry mustard and the remaining salt.
Pour mixture over the cheese. Sprinkle with paprika and bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix this mixture and put into the potatoes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with a little more cheese.
Sprinkle 2 cups of corn flake crumbs on top and drizzle 1/4 cup of margarine over the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lore's pecan pie
directions: Line 10-inch pie plate with pastry.
Boil sugar and syrup together for about 2 minutes.
Pour slowly over slightly beaten eggs, stirring vigorously.
Add butter, vanilla, rum, salt and nut meats.
Pour into unbaked pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° until golden brown.

title: granny's blackberry pudding
directions: In 4
quart
casserole,
cream	the
following:
sugar, butter, flour,
salt,
baking
powder and milk.
Stir well and then pour
in blackberries.
Add boiling water.
Place in oven and cook at
350° until golden brown.
Serve hot, spooning the berries and juice from bottom over the top.

title: crunchy cabbage salad
directions: Mix above ingredients and add dressing.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Drain and mash well. Mix stuffing with margarine and put half over bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix soup, sour cream, pimiento and pepper.
Mix with squash and onion mixture.
Pour over stuffing and sprinkle remaining stuffing over squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese-tomato grill
directions: Cut each tomato into 3 thick slices.
Broil on one side and turn.
Mix cheeses; add salt and pepper.
Spread generously on tomato slices.
Broil until golden brown and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup and milk in casserole dish. Cook Stove Top stuffing according to directions on box.
Add chicken to soup and milk mixture.
Mix well so that all chicken is coated.
Cover chicken mixture with stuffing (do not mix).
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until stuffing gets brown on top. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Cut bacon slices in half.
Wrap around a bunch of green beans and secure with a toothpick to fasten.
Make a glaze from the oleo, brown sugar, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour over beans. Bake covered at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover the last few minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix well with hands. Form into 1 inch balls. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: favorite iced tea
directions: You will need a 1-gallon container.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cook and stir until it starts to thicken, then add zucchini, peppers and onions.
Mix well.
Cook and stir slowly for 30 minutes.
Put in hot jars at once.
If zucchini are small, do not remove the seeds.
Do not peel, big or little.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Whip together powdered sugar and butter until creamy.
Beat in eggs until mixture is fluffy.
Add vanilla and mix.
Spread mixture over crust.
Top with sliced bananas and drained, crushed pineapple.
Frost with Cool Whip. Add cherries and chopped nuts.

title: morning paradise
directions: Heat large skillet on high.
Fry onions, peppers then mushrooms in margarine.
Then add meat.
Scramble eggs with milk and spices. Add to skillet after veggies and meat are fried to your liking. Let simmer for 2 to 4 minutes.
Turn on broiler to 350°.
Add Provolone slices to cover most of egg surface (use whole slices). Then top cheese with diced tomatoes.
Put skillet under broiler for 2 to 4 minutes until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam.
Roll out biscuits or rolls and put in pan.
Put crumbled sausage over biscuits.
Spread cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over cheese.
Salt and pepper.
Add onions if desired.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 350° for 27 to 30 minutes.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except corn chips.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm sprinkled with grated cheese as a dip for corn chips.

title: sunshine slush
directions: In 2-quart freezer container, stir together thawed juice concentrates and corn syrup.
Stir in water and rum.
Seal container and freeze overnight.
Before serving, thaw 30 to 60 minutes or until slushy.
Fill glasses 2/3 full with slush.
Top with club soda and stir gently.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake in bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and poppy seed in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix crackers and butter.
Prepare rice according to directions.
Place rice in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread bite size pieces of chicken across rice.
Pour soup mixture on top of chicken.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey surprise
directions: Melt shortening.
Add garlic and saute slightly.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add broth or chicken bouillon (2 cubes in 2 cups boiling water), soy sauce, turkey and seasonings.
Cook until thickened, about 20 minutes. Serve over cooked rice, fried noodles or biscuits.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Using pastry blender, cut in butter until consistency of coarse meal.
Add milk and egg.
Stir with fork until soft dough forms.
Turn onto floured surface. Knead gently 10 to 12 times.
Roll to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with 2 inch cutter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: diane's hash brown casserole
directions: Combine hash browns and onion.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Combine cream of chicken soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over hash brown mixture.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Dribble margarine over flakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water; drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.
Mix dressing, mustard and garlic together; pour over salad.
Toss gently.
Chill.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: copper pennies
directions: Steam or boil carrots until barely tender. Fold in onions and peppers. In a separate bowl, mix together oil, vinegar, sugar, tomato soup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Add to vegetables and marinate for 2 to 3 days.

title: vegetable okra gumbo
directions: In a large skillet fry bacon crisp, then remove.
Add chopped onion, pepper and okra to bacon grease.
Cook 15 minutes until okra is slightly browned.
Add tomatoes and bacon (broken up in 1-inch pieces), sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover skillet and simmer 15 minutes.
Gumbo should have consistency of stewed tomatoes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Mix 3/4 of cream soups with rice; put on bottom of casserole.
Lay in chicken breasts.
Cover with remaining cream soup, mixed with water.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 90 minutes at 375°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain well.
Bring water, milk, salt and pepper to a boil; add instant potatoes.
Stir with a fork.
Mix potatoes and ground beef together.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with cheese slices.
Lightly brown cheese in oven.

title: saffron rice
directions: Butter inside of 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Place ingredients inside. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Leave lid off the last 10 minutes.

title: french onion scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook in microwave on High for about 8 minutes in 2 tablespoons water.
Meanwhile, make white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese and onion dip.
Let cheese melt and stir until smooth.
Drain potatoes and place in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: "dirt cake"
directions: You will also need 1 tin flower pot or sand bucket, garden trowel for server and gummy worms.

title: spicy bean dip
directions: Saute onion.
Add 3 cans of soup and enough water so it will be dip consistency.
Add olives.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook cubed eggplant in salted water; drain.
Add bread crumbs, tomatoes and corn.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add to eggplant mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Put in greased casserole; top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Season to taste.
Spread in greased pie plate.
Mix Bisquick, eggs and milk until almost smooth.
Pour over meat.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes, until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This will work well in a crock-pot.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix
butter,
sugar, eggs, coconut, raisins and pecans. Pour into shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Put in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then reduce to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hash brown hash
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, cook onion and butter or margarine covered on 100% power (High) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in potatoes, beef, parsley (if desired), Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, on high about 3 minutes or until heated through.
Stir together evaporated milk and flour, then stir in the meat mixture.
Cook uncovered on high about 3 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring each minute until the mixture starts to thicken, then stirring every 30 seconds.
Cook, uncovered, on high for 1 minute more.
Serve atop green pepper wedges, if desired.
Serves 2.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in a baking dish; fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs, shortening and buttermilk; mix well and put in covered container.
When ready to use, fill cupcake tin 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Will keep 6 weeks and gets tastier at end.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix and pour over first half of bread cubes.
Add remaining cubes.
Beat 2 eggs slightly and add 1 1/2 c. milk and pour over top of mixture and let stand 1 hour or over night.
When ready to use, spoon 1 can of cream of mushroom soup over.
Sprinkle buttered cubes over top.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in saucepan.
Saute onion in butter.
Add consomme and garlic powder.
Simmer on low for 30 to 45 minutes.
Pour into soup bowls; add croutons and shredded cheese.
Heat under broiler until cheese melts.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: tasty tetrazzini
directions: Cook linguini; rinse in colander with hot water.
Return to pot; mix with melted butter and mushrooms (melt butter with garlic).
Mix soup with milk.
Add to noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (generous).
Garnish with parsley.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick of margarine.
Put mixture in bottom of dish.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and 2 sticks of melted margarine for 15 minutes and pour in crust.
Slice bananas on top of filling; drain pineapple and put on bananas; top with Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Put the 6 peppers in a pan with sides like a cake pan. After the mixture is mixed together, put into the peppers. Top with ketchup. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until ketchup on top is cooked until brown.

title: cherry freeze
directions: Combine all except topping.
Fold in topping.
Put in a flat dish.
Cover and freeze.
Take out of freezer about 10 minutes before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients (fold in Cool Whip) together.
Layer wafers, bananas and mixture in layers.
Cover with small carton of Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pickled fresh ginger
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 or 2 minutes, depending on thickness of ginger slices.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Keeps for several weeks.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread each of the ingredients in a large oblong Pyrex baking dish in order listed.
Do not mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add seasoning mix and water; simmer 5 minutes.

title: cheese omelet
directions: Heat butter in 9-inch pie plate on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Turn plate to coat bottom with butter.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie plate.
Cook, covered with plastic wrap.
Cook on Medium for 2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until omelet is almost set.
Stir after 1 minute.
Let stand, covered, for 2 minutes.
With a spatula, loosen edges of omelet from plate.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup shredded cheese down center.
Fold into thirds to serve.

title: creole eggplant("southern living cooking light" cookbook)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Makes 6 servings (about 38 calories per serving).

title: scalloped mushroom potatoes
directions: Combine soup and milk until well blended.
Add cheese, pimento, mushrooms and salt.
Blend well.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are tender when pierced with a fork.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in a large saucepan over medium heat until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer on low, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: saccharin and mustard pickles
directions: Dissolve your salt, mustard, alum and saccharin in small amount of hot vinegar, stirring very well.
Place dissolved brine in 2 gallon jars.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion in large skillet.
Add catsup, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and salt, stirring to combine.
Combine sauce with pork and beans, lima beans, butter beans and kidney beans.
Cook, covered, in 2 1/2-quart casserole in slow oven (325°) for 30 minutes.
Remove:
cover and continue cooking 30 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: one-dish ham bake
directions: Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix baking mix and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Bake 30 minutes or until light golden brown, at 450°.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in shallow dish.
Combine 1 cup water, vinegar and dressing mix in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over vegetables, tossing lightly to coat.
Cover and chill overnight.
Serve on leaf lettuce.

title: spiced shrimp kebabs
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/4 cup syrup.
In skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Saute garlic, spice and tomato paste 2 minutes.
Add shrimp; saute 2 minutes.
Stir in pineapple syrup and remaining ingredients; boil.
Add pineapple place in bowl. Accompany with picks to make kebabs.

title: rosie's homemade sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well; knead together, cover and refrigerate for three days.
On the fourth day, shape into three or four 6-inch rolls.
Bake at 150° for ten hours or 185° for eight hours on broiler rack pan so that it is not laying in its own grease.
Wrap in Saran Wrap, foil, etc.
Refrigerate.
Will keep in refrigerator for seven to ten days or freeze.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar and cream together until fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts; beat well.
Sift flour and salt together in a separate bowl and set aside.

title: horseradish dressing
directions: In a blender, blend well everything but chives.
Add chives after blending with spoon.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: zucchini mortola
directions: Peel zucchini.
Cut in half and half again.
Boil in salted water for about 5 minutes, then drain well.
Put on bottom of a greased dish.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Blend together.
Press down mixture into a 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions.
Add pineapple to unset pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: creamy parmesan-pepper dressing(low-fat)
directions: Place the cottage cheese in a food processor.
Process for 3 minutes or until very smooth.
With the machine running, pour in the buttermilk and vinegar.
Process until smooth.
Add the Parmesan and pepper.
Blend briefly to distribute evenly.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Immerse cabbage in boiling water; boil 5 minutes.
Plunge in ice water.
Peel off limp outer leaves and repeat process.
Drain leaves (10 to 15 leaves).
Chop remaining cabbage and place in large bowl.
Peel and mince onion and add to chopped cabbage.
Add ground beef, seasonings, garlic, egg, 1/2 cup tomato puree, bread crumbs, salt and pepper and blend thoroughly.
Place about 1/4 cup beef mixture in cup part of cabbage leaf.
Carefully fold over sides and roll up.
Place all cabbage rolls in roasting pan.
Add remaining tomato puree to pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple butter spice bread
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease
a
9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sift
together
flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add
sugar,
eggs
and
oil;
stir to blend.
Fold in apple butter,
pecans
and
raisins.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.	Let cool in pan for 15 minutes, then turn out
onto wire rack to cool completely.
Makes nice gifts for holidays.

title: stir and drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar and oil; add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Drop by tablespoon.
Butter the bottom of a drinking glass and dip in sugar.
Smash cookie.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch closely and remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: almond cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream shortening; add egg and almond extract.
Gradually add dry ingredients and mix well. Roll into 1 inch balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Press in one almond in center of cookie.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 50 cookies.
Note:
Sesame seed may be used instead of almonds.

title: quick skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat and drain.
Stir in seasonings, Veg-All, broth and macaroni.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream and 1/2 the French fried onions.
Heat through.
Do not boil.
Top with remaining onions.

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin and cinnamon red hots.
Stir until all are dissolved.
Chill until gelatin is almost set.
Whip thickened gelatin at low speed of electric mixer for a few seconds, then gradually beat in cold evaporated milk.
Turn mixer speed to high and whip until gelatin mixture is double in volume. Fold in apples, marshmallows and walnuts, lightly but thoroughly. Turn into mold (5-cup) that is lightly oiled.
Chill until firm, about 4 to 5 hours.

title: special k bars
directions: Cook brown sugar, white syrup and margarine for 2 minutes. Add peanut butter.
Pour over Special K.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: mardi gras cake
directions: Melt morsels in water.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk and morsels.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Stir in flour.
Roll dough on floured surface.
Add additional flour if necessary.
Cut into shapes.

title: california carrots
directions: Pare carrots; cut diagonally in thin slices.
Combine with raisins, water and salt in a medium-size heavy saucepan; cover. Heat to boiling, then simmer 30 minutes, or until carrots are tender, drain.
Sprinkle with brown sugar; add butter and lemon juice.
Heat slowly until butter melts, then cook, stirring often, 10 minutes, or until carrots are richly glazed.

title: mississippi mud brownies(microwave)
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart mixing bowl.
Microwave on High 1 minute or until butter melts.
Stir in sugar and eggs; set aside. Combine flour, salt and cocoa. Stir well.
Stir dry mixture into egg mixture. Stir in vanilla and pecans.

Spread batter in a greased and floured 8-inch square baking dish. Shield corners with triangles of aluminum foil, keeping foil smooth and close to dish. Place dish atop a microwave-safe cereal bowl inverted in the oven.

Microwave on Medium (50% power) 6 to 7 minutes, giving dish a half turn after 3 minutes. Remove shields; microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until top is almost dry. Remove from oven and place directly on countertop to cool.
Sprinkle marshmallows over brownies; cover with aluminum foil.
Let stand 2 minutes. Remove foil. Spread with Chocolate Frosting.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 16 brownies.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons broth 5 to 7 minutes or until softened over medium-high heat. Add tomato sauce, honey, oregano, basil and white pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer gently for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cream muffins
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients alternately with sour cream; add to egg mixture.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon in greased muffin tins or paper cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 24 muffins (large).

title: iced coffee special
directions: Make a pot of your favorite flavored coffee or regular and turn off heat immediately after it is brewed.
Let sit about 20 minutes.
Pour into a covered pitcher and place in refrigerator for at least 1 hour (the colder the better).
When you want a cool refreshing drink, put some ice in a tall glass.
Pour coffee in with milk and Sweet 'N Low to your taste.
I usually put 1/2 packet of Sweet 'N Low and 3 tablespoons milk.
Stir and enjoy!

title: easy steak supreme
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and stir.
Cook on low all day.
Serve on rice.

title: cucumber-radish dressing
directions: Stir all ingredients. Chill 1 hour. Serve with mixed greens. Make about 1 cup. Prep time: 10 minutes.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Grease 2 pie plates.
Blend eggs, sugar, flour and margarine. Add milk and coconut.
Pour into greased pie plates and bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: marinade for vegetables
directions: Mix marinade ingredients in a very large bowl.

Gently stir in celery sticks, carrot sticks, bell pepper rings, onion rings, 1 pound of mushrooms, green and black olives, a small jar of pimentos, cauliflower, cherry tomatoes (halved) and broccoli. Refrigerate 6 to 12 hours, re-mixing occasionally.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, oil and salt.
Add rest of ingredients and marinate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat the eggs. Add sugar, flour and baking powder together. Add vanilla. The last thing you add before baking is the hot milk. Bake at 350° until done.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown beef. Pour off grease.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat slowly until bouillon cube is dissolved.
Transfer to large mixing bowl before adding noodles.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°
for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: pearl's bars
directions: Cut cookie roll in half and slice each half.
Place half of the slices in the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan and press to cover. Beat the other ingredients together and spread in the pan.
Then cover with the remaining slices of dough.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool then cut into squares.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: scandinavian almond bars
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, beat butter or margarine until softened.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and almond extract; beat well.
Add flour mixture; beat until well mixed.
Divide dough into fourths.
Form each into a 12-inch roll.
Place two rolls 4 to 5 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten until 3 inches wide.
Repeat with remaining rolls.
Brush flattened rolls with milk; sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in a 325° oven for 12 to 14 minutes, or until edges are lightly browned.
While cookies are still warm, cut them crosswise at a diagonal into 1-inch strips.
Cool.
Drizzle with Almond Icing.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: cool summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
A few drops of green food coloring may be added, if desired.	Place in refrigerator until chilled.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: best apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Add chopped apples and nuts and bake in greased jelly roll pan or 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, peppers, cucumbers and grapefruit in bowl.
Add French dressing.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: swedish pepparkaka slices(ginger slices)
directions: In large bowl, sift flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Set aside.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and cream well.
Blend in molasses.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Shape dough into balls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for several hours. When dough is stiff, cut into quarters.
Roll out 1 quarter; take cookie cutters (any you have available) and cut out cookies with floured cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: my mom's coffee bars
directions: Sift together first five ingredients.
Cream next three then add alternately flour and coffee.
Add vanilla, dates (cut up) and nuts (in small pieces).
Pour into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done, like a cake.
Cook, then sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Cut in bars and try and eat just one!

title: applesauce date cake
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Add eggs, brown sugar, margarine and 1 cup hot applesauce.
Beat until combined on low speed of mixer; then beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add remaining applesauce, dates and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: old fashion cornmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie pastry.
Cook very slowly, at about 300°, until thick.
Use 1 teaspoon flavoring. Test with toothpick.
Old, old recipe but very, very good.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in butter or margarine. Add soups, tomatoes and chicken. Layer bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with soup mixture. Add a layer of tortillas and 1/2 of the cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: tasty chex mix(will stay fresh 5 to 7 weeks)
directions: Melt margarine and add next four ingredients.
In large turkey sized roaster pan, mix together remaining ingredients.

title: noodle ting-a-lings
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Mix in peanuts and noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Slice top off of bread and hollow out, saving bread pieces. Mix rest of ingredients, pour into hollow bread and put top back on. Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for one hour. Use bread pieces, crackers or chips for dipping.

title: spring salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil and vinegar; bring to boil, then let cool. Drain the white corn, green beans and peas; put in large bowl. Chop or slice to taste the green pepper, celery and onion (small pieces are better).
Mix the sugar mixture and vegies together. Cover; let set overnight, chilled.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix brown sugar and Miracle Whip together; spread this on top of layers.
Sprinkle cheese on top of Miracle Whip mixture, then top with bacon.
Best if made a few hours ahead.

title: banana fudge walnut brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Grease bottom only of 8-inch square pan. Melt in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, the butter and chocolate chips. Beat in thoroughly with spoon the flour, sugar, walnuts, banana, vanilla, baking powder, salt and egg. Spread batter evenly in pan. Bake about 30 minutes or until center is set.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes one 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 2 loaf pans.

title: chili
directions: Cut up bacon in 1/4-1/2 inch pieces with kitchen shears. Brown bacon and ground meat together until cooked through.
If using ground chuck, drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer for at least an hour.

title: spaghetti supper pie
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed and drain.
Add eggs, Parmesan and parsley.
In a greased 9-inch pie plate, layer half of the spaghetti, then half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Heat sauce; add mushrooms.
Cut pie into wedges and serve with sauce over top.

title: the chewy oatmeal cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended and fluffy.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheets. Remove to rack.

title: ritz-broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in casserole.
Mix onion, mayonnaise, cheese, egg, mushroom soup and pimento together and pour over broccoli. Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until lightly browned and set.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli as directed and drain. Mix soup with milk.
Bring water to boiling; add dressing mix and cut margarine.
Mix.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer broccoli, soup mixture and dressing mixture.
Repeat.
Top with shredded cheese (optional).
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Form quarter size balls and press down on cookie sheet with a water tumbler that has been dampened and then dipped in sugar.
Bake at 300° until golden, about 25 minutes.

title: white chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together until fluffy the first 5 ingredients.
Mix together next 5 ingredients and add to above mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts to batter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 6 or 7 minutes at 375°.

title: laredo supper
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with corn chips.

title: baked pasta supreme
directions: Cook rigatoni; keep warm.
In skillet, brown sausage, breaking up until no pink remains.
Drain thoroughly.
Reserve meat.
In medium size bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, nutmeg, salt, pepper and parsley.
Set aside.
Generously grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon 1/3 sauce over bottom of pan.

On top of sauce, spread even layers of 1/2 cooked rigatoni, then all of cooked sausage, then Ricotta mix, then remaining cooked rigatoni, then remaining tomato sauce and finally Parmesan sprinkled evenly over all.
Cover with foil. Preheat oven to 400°; bake, covered, 15 minutes.
Remove cover; bake another 5 to 10 minutes or until mixture is browned and bubbling.

title: waldorf salad with raisins
directions: In medium bowl place in diced apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add celery, raisins and salt.
Blend in mayonnaise and sour cream.
Pour over fruit and toss.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; set aside.

title: ern's skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Brown beef in large skillet; remove and cook macaroni, onions and pepper in meat fat until macaroni is yellow.

Return beef to skillet; add tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and Worcestershire. Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until macaroni is cooked to suit. If it cooks out too dry another can of tomato sauce can be added. Very good either way.

title: cornbread
directions: Stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat just until smooth (do not overbeat). Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 or 9 servings.

title: strawberry streusel muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line muffin cups with paper liners. Sift together flour, sugar, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into medium bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Put the egg, melted butter and milk in the well.
Stir until combined. Quickly stir in strawberries and lemon zest.
Fill each cup 3/4 full with batter.

title: snowflake fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese until fluffy; add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and debone; cut into small pieces.
Save the broth, then cook noodles in broth the chicken was cooked in. Mix in a large bowl the cream of chicken, corn and sour cream. Stir in egg noodles and chicken.
Mix together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch covered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oven lemon chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces in mixture of flour and paprika.
Melt butter in baking pan, add chicken pieces and coat evenly with butter.
Arrange in a single layer.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces and pour basting sauce over them. Continue baking until chicken is brown and tender, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: magic no-mix bars
directions: Combine and bake in the same pan.
Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Add cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour over entire mixture the milk.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes or until slightly browned.
Cool 15 minutes.
Makes 32 bars.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Slice top off whole package of rolls.
Layer ham and sliced cheese.
Put top back on rolls.
Cut into separate pieces.
Stir other ingredients into melted margarine.
Pour over rolls and let set for 30 minutes, or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas, then combine dry ingredients. Fold in nuts. Bake in two small or 1 large loaf pan.
The pans should be half full.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate mint fluff
directions: Put cookies through food chopper.
Pack crumbs into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Keep some for topping.
Soak gelatin in milk for 1 hour.
Beat egg yolks, sugar and salt in top of double boiler. Add gelatin and cook until thick (5 to 7 minutes); cool thoroughly. Beat egg whites stiff.
Whip cream with vanilla and few drops food coloring.
Fold egg yolks mixed with egg whites and whipped cream. Pour into pan; put crumbs on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water to Jell-O, stir until dissolved.
Add Coca-Cola, stir in pineapple, cream cheese (cut up) and nuts. Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce (optional).
Makes 8 servings of about 1/2-cup each.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine first nine ingredients in a saucepan; cook and stir constantly over medium heat until cheese melts. Stir in crabmeat and remaining ingredients. Transfer to dish and keep warm.

title: plum cake
directions: Blend together flour, sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Place quartered potatoes in shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 450° for 60 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine chicken, tomatoes, potatoes, onion and okra in 5-quart crock-pot.
Set on low and cook 8 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Add corn, ketchup and barbecue sauce.
Cook 10 more minutes and serve.

title: sour cream n' chive pop corn
directions: Combine pop corn and butter.
Sprinkle sauce mix over buttered pop corn.
Stir until mix is well distrubuted.

title: family favorite
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package. Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Combine ingredients. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: herbed cheese spread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and butter until smooth. Add the parsley, chives, chervil, garlic, tarragon and lemon-pepper; mix well.
Transfer to a serving dish.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
Remove from the refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers. Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: lemon pineapple ring
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet, a spoonful at a time, stirring until melted.
Add undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cottage cheese.
Pour into 6 1/2-cup ring mold. Chill until set.
Unmold onto serving platter. Center can be filled with fruit or decorated with mint leaves.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash and mash.
Put slices of bread in dish and add warm milk.
When bread is soft, add hot squash and the rest of the ingredients except bread crumbs.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 2-quart casserole.
Spread crumbs over top and put back in oven and brown.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer. Pour into buttered pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 min.

title: no-bake strawberry bottom cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Beat sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spread thin layer of glaze over bottom of crust.
Place strawberry slices on glaze and cover with another thin layer of glaze.
Gently spoon mixture over glazed berries in crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In 9 x 12-inch pan, melt butter.
Stir in macaroni to coat. Cover with grated cheese.
Stir.
Salt and pepper.
Pour milk over all.
Do not stir while baking.
Cook 1 1/2 hours on 350°.

title: bolts and nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 250° for about 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: no bake hawaiian cream pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate several hours (at least 3 hours) and serve.
This is a cool and refreshing dessert and very easy to prepare.

title: shrimp-olive salad
directions: Mix together and add dressing, salt and pepper.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown all meat.
Chop all onion.
Combine in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except soup.
Form into meatballs.
Brown in skillet.
Pour soup over browned meatballs and simmer.
Quick and easy.

title: ranch beans
directions: In large Dutch oven on medium heat, brown diced bacon.
Pour off excess grease.
Use rest to saute onion rings until soft. Stir in all remaining ingredients; add bacon.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring often.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350°, uncovered, one hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in a greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad(italian style)
directions: Cook pasta (don't overcook).
Drain and put in large bowl. Add tomato sauce and Italian dressing.
Cut the rest of the ingredients into bite size pieces; add everything together and toss.
Chill at least 1 hour; toss again before serving.
(The longer it chills, the better!!!)

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together; set aside.
With mixer, mix eggs, margarine, milk, vanilla and bananas.
Slowly add dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Fill pans 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Check with toothpick.

title: grandma's favorite stuffing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except broth, butter and eggs.
Toss ingredients well.
Add broth, butter and eggs.
Mix well.
Use to stuff neck and body cavities of turkey or for ease in preparation and serving.
Cook separately in a well-greased baking dish or casserole during the last 45 minutes of roasting time.

title: cheese souffle for two
directions: In a small saucepan, over medium-high heat, melt butter. Blend in flour and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk, all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture boils and is smooth and thickened.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Set aside.

title: fried rice
directions: In large skillet, melt 3/4 stick of margarine.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Add beaten egg and sliced mushrooms.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Add cooked rice and mix well.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic salt and more soy sauce if needed.
If rice seems dry, add remaining margarine.

title: favorite popcorn snack
directions: Mix together in large bowl or plastic bag.
This is a Welcome School favorite, it's not messy!

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Melt shortening; let cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water (not hot).
Mix all dry ingredients together, then add all the liquids to form dough.
Roll out on floured surface; cut with a large biscuit cutter.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Can be dotted with butter.
Makes about 24 large biscuits.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Pat dry pork tenderloin (usually long tubular in shape and packaged with two together).
Rub on Dijon mustard to meat; coat approximately 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle with tarragon, approximately 1 teaspoon per pound. Wrap tenderloin with bacon. Use toothpicks to secure two pieces together. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes per pound or until cooked to 160°.

title: pie crust
directions: Fold in egg and milk mixture into flour, then fold in lard to become firm. Roll out 1/4 of dough for one pie crust.
Yields 4 pie crusts.

title: florentine potatoes
directions: Saute onion and pepper, in butter until soft. Add potatoes, saute 2 minutes. Add tomatoes. Cook over high heat until slightly thickened. Add spinach, heat through. Sprinkle with Cheese.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Layer bottom of pie crust with sugar and peanut butter mixture.
Save a little to decorate top of pie.
Use vanilla or peanut butter pudding, using 1/4 cup less milk (cooked, instant or frozen).
Spread pudding over crumbs in the pie crust.
Cover with Cool Whip, then place crumbled topping to decorate.

title: peach delight
directions: Put fresh peaches in boiling water for a few minutes.
Remove peel and cut into slices.
Put peach slices in a 2-quart baking dish.
Peaches should reach only halfway up the sides of the baking dish.

title: chilie rellenos casserole
directions: Spray pan.
Lay whole chilies in pan.
Stuff each chilie with chunk of Jack cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, flour and seasonings.
Pour over chilies and put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Combine zucchini, egg, carrot, onion, cheese, green pepper, 1/4 cup flour and salt and pepper and mix well.
Shape this mixture into patties, whatever size you choose and coat them with a mixture of 1/4 cup flour and 1 1/2 cups cornflake crumbs.
Fry patties in a skillet with hot oil until brown.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix taco seasoning, corn and beans with juice into meat.
Crumble chips in bottom of long casserole pan.
Pour meat mixture over chips and bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top and heat until melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on crackers.

title: mexican tossed salad
directions: Place tomatoes, beans and onions in a large salad bowl.
Toss gently.
Layer lettuce on top.
Can be covered at this step and refrigerated.
Just before serving, add cheese, corn chips and dressing.
Toss and serve.

title: homemade mustard
directions: Cook in double boiler until done.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients well in a medium size mixing bowl.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and nuts.
Work together well with fork; spread over the bottom of large baking dish (13 1/2 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Set aside to cool. Cream the cheese, adding sugar; fold in small carton Cool Whip. Spread over cooled first layer.
Mix chocolate pudding using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Spread over second layer.
Spread large carton Cool Whip on top for final layer.
Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours before serving.
May sprinkle chopped pecans or chocolate curls on top.

title: gramma's irish soda bread
directions: In a huge bowl, stir first 4 ingredients.
In another bowl, cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir creamed mixture into the flour along with buttermilk.
This will be very stiff and heavy. Stir in caraway and raisins.
Spoon into buttered heavy casserole dish.
Cut an X on top.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: super quick buns
directions: Lay open each hot dog bun.
Put 1 slice of ham and cheese. Pull bun closed and push shredded lettuce on top.
Sprinkle with garlic powder (to taste).
Pour a teaspoon of dressing on top. Stick 2 toothpicks in bun to hold together.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Microwave just until cheese melts.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass or plastic bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavor.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Mix pineapple, oranges and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle dry jello over pineapple mixture.
Fold in one 8 ounce Cool Whip (easy). Refrigerate in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower, pepper and onion into bite size. Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: no bake peanut butter logs
directions: Combine powdered sugar and butter in large mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer until smooth. Stir in peanut butter and cereal (mixing with hands if needed). Shape into 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch logs. Chill. Spread tops of cookies with your choice of frosting.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and lard; add egg.
Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: quick pineapple pie
directions: In a cake pan empty contents of can of pineapple with juice. Then evenly spread powder cake mix over pineapple.
Melt butter in microwave or in a pan over low heat.
Pour melted butter over the contents in cake pan.
Then bake in oven at 325°
until lightly brown.

title: healthy brown rice
directions: Combine brown rice and sweet rice in a pot.
Rinse the rice a couple of times.
Pour in water, add salt and soak for about 1 hour.
Cover and cook on medium heat until it boils, then lower heat and cook for about 45 minutes.
Turn off the heat and leave the pot on the burner for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cake with salad dressing
directions: Mix cocoa in hot water.
Mix all ingredients together
and beat well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°, about 30 minutes.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add milk, flour, egg and baking powder.

title: mom's sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix together and heat. Serve over rice, meatballs, chicken or ribs.

title: best ever muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening. Add milk. Chill dough for 30 minutes in refrigerator. After dough has been chilled, roll out dough to 1/8-inch thick and cut into strips. Drop into soup.

title: basil chicken medley
directions: Heat oil in skillet; saute garlic.
Add chicken and cook until no longer pink; remove and keep warm.
Combine remaining ingredients, except rice or pasta.
Toss to coat vegetables well. Add to skillet and stir-fry about 3 to 5 minutes.
